reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Been here since its inception. A decent place run by a guy who previously used to make bajjis and bondas in the same neighbourhood.
You get fresh served south Indian dishes in the morning and they make amazing sambar I tell.

The best part being that they make benne masala dosa (Butter Masala Dosa) and damn he does it great.

Apart from this in the noon they serve meals which are pretty decent for the price and have tried it about 3-4 times.

In the evening they make Chinese dishes which are really well prepared and I am always visiting the place for breakfast and almost every Sunday
??.

They also make these specialty food like mangalore buns and other desserts like halwas which are good try as well .

They have both standing and sitting options and the food is worth the price.

Only thing I'm hoping for is for delivery options which would make it better.")]

address: 15, Bannerghatta Main Road, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Le Arabia
dish_liked: Chicken Biryani
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

reviews_list:

Overall great food and a friendly, polite host. Must visit if in this side of town!:)'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered for the first time from Hotel Brundavan yesterday for dinner. Schezwan Noodles was tasty, very much like home made. Roti was good and surprised to see palak dal as a side dish. Brundavan special dosa was very nice and heavy too, loved the ginger chutney and coconut chutney. Sambhar was not that fresh, so jus ignored it and disposed too. Along with all these items i ordered Paneer Chilly as a starter which was quite a disappointed one. Paneer pieces were so hard and wasn't fresh. I really couldn't enjoy starter as it could have been better. Overall, i will rate order as 3 out of 5. It was nice on the whole.")]

name: Bangalore Pantry
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated near Hulimavi hate, this has become our lunch spot as it's very close to college. Most of their food is good. It should be among the most pocket friendly places around here. Good food, service might get delayed during lunch hours as it gets very crowded.

Kerala porota is a must try here. Their veg n non-veg curries are all good. Chicken Hyderabadi Biryani is also a good option here. I like their chicken shawarma as well. Overall a good, pocket friendly restaurant.

I wouldn't recommend their malabari chicken biryani because is basically chicken mixed in ghee rice. Their Chinese menu is just decent. Also the Chinese main course I have tried, the chicken was very hard. Their juices tasted very good the first time I tried but later on it became too watery.")]

[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated near Hulimavi hate, this has become our lunch spot as it's very close to college. Most of their food is good. It should be among the most pocket friendly places around here. Good food, service might get delayed during lunch hours as it gets very crowded.

Kerala porota is a must try here. Their veg n non-veg curries are all good. Chicken Hyderabadi Biryani is also a good option here. I like their chicken shawarma as well. Overall a good, pocket friendly restaurant.

I wouldn't recommend their malabari chicken biryani because is basically chicken mixed in ghee rice. Their Chinese menu is just decent. Also the Chinese main course I have tried, the chicken was very hard. Their juices tasted very good the first time I tried but later on it became too watery.")]

[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This huge property located in the heart of JP Nagar can host about 2k people in their different sections. The voluminous of the place makes it very attractive.
Tasted their 3 brews(wit, klosh, IPA) and was not a fan of it.
They have a huge spread of veg and non veg starters, tried the veg nachos, ghee roast panner and kurkure kabba. These starters were of good quantity and tasted good too. Would recommend the ghee roast.
All in all a great place with good service and superb food. Can improve on the brewed beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Unique starters and great ambience . I don't drink, but the guzzlers say the brew is gud, as for me the mock tails were really gud and the overall experience was relaxing and yet you could catch the beat and the feel of the brewery will really engulf you."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Another brewery for the thirsty people to find solace.... big place and various sitting arrangements and ambience. Being a vegetarian and teatoddler does not give much leeway with the options to offer. Started with broccoli soup which was pleasant but that u can't it anywhere as. Not sure if I would be going there again and might stick to hakuna ma tata instead."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place.. the micro brewery serves freshly brewed beer. There needs to be more on the beer menu to offer though. The bar menu is good..

All in all good place to hang out and have a few beers!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

Seating chairs I felt were a bit wobbly and u might just fall off if u drink one too many..

Some one who loves visiting new breweries has something to look forward for..

.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ok this place was creating a lot of buzz so decided to go.

  One of a kind place in JP Nagar. Huge open space that's not on a rooftop, hard to find in Bangalore! Seating modules with different ambience spread over multiple blocks and levels, gives anyone the kind of space they want.

Service was top notch, very well attended by the staff and all orders were served pretty quick despite the huge crowd on a weekend night.

South Indian starters we tried are excellent. But the continental/fusion starters were average. 7 Spices, a chef special was a bit disappointment with the BBQ sauce overpowering spices.   Nice place! I got a feeling of it being sort of a 'resort' than a pub. We for instance had plenty of seating options to choose from, we chose one near the pool. Ordered for Chicken Nachos which had generous amount of meat in it and tasted fine. The Jerk Chicken I think should have been accompanied with some interesting dips to go with, it tasted pretty plain to me. The pizza Polloala Griglia was good. address: 57, 1st Main Rd, Sarakki Industrial Layout, 3rd Phase, JP Nagar, Bengaluru
name: Levitate Brewery and Kitchen
dish_liked: Wheat Beer, Lager, Paneer Lollipop, Rustica Pizza, Dark Beer, Mocktails, Cocktails
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls. 
Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.
 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls. 
Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.

  So, it was the new year's Eve and we were expecting to spend a nice evening with music drinks and dinner.

Overall a lovely place to head to in jp nagar.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice ambience, good food and great beers. Being a new outlet, lot of improvements and focus is needed on the service front. I celebrated my birthday today, so happy and have good memories to take forward - except the cake which was really watery and tasted below average ?. All the best guys and I am sure over the days/weeks to come, you will turn things around.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A new kid on the block..First of all a great location opp Mini forest. Superb Ambience specially on the rooftop floor. Decent music and good range of in-house beers.. 
Amazing gamut of food on the menu, quality stuff, quantity can be little better though. Few of the beers on the menu were not available. Initially they refused to serve our single malt order on the bar and told us that it'll be served only on 2nd floor, which was beyond our understanding. To our surprise on insisting he poured from a bottle which was kept with him only. 

We visited last saturday and looked like the mgt was overwhelmed with the turnout. I am giving the benefit of doubt as it's a very new joint so I hope the mgt takes the service as an urgent priority and fixes it asap. There are lot of things to be improved w.r.t. food availability, service & general management but since they've just opened I am expecting them to settle soon."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

address: 24th Main, 7th Phase, Opposite Brigade Palm Springs, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Brahma Brews
dish_liked: Beer, Cocktails, Pizza, Peri Chicken, Belgian Wit, Neer Dosa, Cheese Balls
cuisines: Continental, South Indian, Finger Food, Pizza, Seafood
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This huge property located in the heart of JP Nagar can host about 2k people in their different sections. The voluminous of the place makes it very attractive.
Tasted their 3 brews(wit, klosh, IPA) and was not a fan of it.
They have a huge spread of veg and non veg starters, tried the veg nachos, ghee roast panner and kurkure kabba. These starters were of good quantity and tasted good too. Would recommend the ghee roast.
All in all a great place with good service and superb food. Can improve on the brewed beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Unique starters and great ambience . I don't drink, but the guzzlers say the brew is gud, as for me the mock tails were really gud and the overall experience was relaxing and yet you could catch the beat and the feel of the brewery will really engulf you."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Another brewery for the thirsty people to find solace.... big place and various sitting arrangements and ambience. Being a vegetarian and teatoddler does not give much leeway with the options to offer. Started with broccoli soup which was pleasant but that u can't it anywhere as. The less said about the drumstick soup. The cheese balls and kurkure tikki lacked the flavour and taste. Not sure if I would be going there again and might stick to hakuna ma tata instead."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place.. the micro brewery serves freshly brewed beer. There needs to be more on the beer menu to offer though. The bar menu is good..
The service is quick... Food is also nice, although I would need to try out more dishes to give a robust feedback on food.
Huge seating space and the ambience is key differentiator.

All in all good place to hang out and have a few beers!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  New brew place in town. They didn't have many brew options as mentioned on the menu card. Great ambience. Food options were plenty. Their weizenbock beer was damn nice, must try. Although I wanted to try honey scotch ale, which was not available sadly. We also tried their black n blue cocktail which was okay. Rustica pizza was yum as usual. ?"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Brewery started on the 1st Feb.. crafted beer options in south Bangalore are on a rise..this one apparently is the biggest place at the moment.. huge crowd on weekends..its situated next to hakuna matata..
Their starts were perfectly cooked..chicken biryani may well become their USP..yeah..u must try that...

Seating chairs I felt were a bit wobbly and u might just fall off if u drink one too many..

Staff and service was found to be professional..
Some one who loves visiting new breweries has something to look forward for..
Hope they brew speciality beer else am just too bored to find the same options in every brewery
.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ok this place was creating a lot of buzz so decided to go.
Went there with 9 of my friends and had prior booking but still have to wait for more than half an hour.

Starting with the ambience it's extremely beautiful ? and have a separate corner for couples for candle light dinner.
Only thing that ruined the ambience was there music. As the place is so big but they don't have enough speakers so it results to a flop nightlife.

Don't have enough options in their food menu especially for vegetarians.

But definitely you should visit the place once for it's ambience and it's drinks which is great.

Moreover it's a place for dine."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Had been here on a sat night, a pretty huge place. But feels kind of isolated. They have only 4 beers as of now - Kolsch , IPA, Weizenbock and Belgian Wit. The Belgian wit and wizenbock we're good, Kolsch and IPA not up to the mark. Mushroom chilly fry as a starter is nice."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Got here on a saturday evening/night . Lovely ambience, service was quick . Sweet staff, beer n food was good . Loved the andhra chilli chicken . Huge place . Goood music . Candle light dinner tables were really nice .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One of a kind place in JP Nagar. Huge open space that's not on a rooftop, hard to find in Bangalore! Seating modules with different ambience spread over multiple blocks and levels, gives anyone the kind of space they want.

Service was top notch, very well attended by the staff and all orders were served pretty quick despite the huge crowd on a weekend night.

South Indian starters we tried are excellent. But the continental/fusion starters were average. 7 Spices, a chef special was a bit disappointment with the BBQ sauce overpowering spices. Andhra Chilly Chicken was excellent. They had 4 beers on tap. Belgian Wit was great. Weizenbock was excellent and perfect for the current cool weather. Kolsch was very average, felt a bit watered down with no aftertaste. IPA was not up to the mark, the next batches would improve may be."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A spacious brewery, A much needed requirement in JP Nagar. A perfect place to chill post office hours & a weekend with friends. People dont need to travel far for having fresh brews.
This place is full of greenery, water bodies (such as fountain & pond). The staff is very courteous, the food is lip smacking. We tried a lot of dishes, from veg to non veg, everything was up-to the mark including the presentation & taste. Although the brewery wasnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t functional when I visited, I would be coming to try it again. I would surely recommend this place to everybody.

?? Taste 5/5
?? Ambience 5/5
?? Staff 5/5
?? Value for Money 5/5
?? Hygiene 5/5'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A very big brewery in JP nagar. Lots of open air tables, a section of candle light tables and one section near the fountain.

They have some 6 brew options. Not all will be available. Depends on your luck if you wanna try other than regular wheat beer.

Food was decent. Rates are moderate. 500 ml of beer would close around 275.

Biggest advantage is u dnt have to go all the way to Koramangala or Indiranagar to experience a good time.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Attentive and friendly staff, fantastic alfresco dining with different seating areas, a water fountain, big shiny brewing machinery on display, good alcoholic selection, a bit random with some items on the menu, but overall pretty good fare. Will definitely visit again!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The restaurant needs to look into food quality ,freshness and taste aspects , the place was opened recently the menu card mentioned in Zomato is obsolete.

Customer service is acceptable.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It was on my list from the very 1st day it's opend and finally was there last Saturday with my wife and kid. I wasn't sure wether they wil allow kids or not but I was happy there wre no restriction as Such. What a beautiful place it is, Massive and almost whole place is open which is mind blowing. Food was definitely something on they they have to work on... wasn't very happy with food. Beer was superb and I had very good time for sure.wil visit again this week. And wil recommend other as well to visit"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Nice place! I got a feeling of it being sort of a 'resort' than a pub. Its huge, spacious with a lot of open area and has various sections of seating, it even gave me an impression like the place could never appear crowded even if it were filled to capacity- which I doubt could happen as theres so much seating space that there could always be room to accomodate guests even if it were a weekend. We for instance had plenty of seating options to choose from, we chose one near the pool. Ordered for Chicken Nachos which had generous amount of meat in it and tasted fine. The Jerk Chicken I think should have been accompanied with some interesting dips to go with, it tasted pretty plain to me. The pizza Polloala Griglia was good. Finally the dessert 'Chocolate Surprise' was pretty inventive but I didn't fall for the Indian Sweet Meat + Chocolate combination. It was overall a good experience because the ambience is simply lovely- classy infact to also bring families into. Recommend it."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Tiny place right above Slimsins cafe. Chinese style bhel was super tasty and innovative. Kulcha taco was kind of. If you are visiting this place then definitely try Chinese style bhel.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

name: @ The Bbq
cuisines: BBQ, Continental, North Indian, Chinese, Beverages
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A quite good place in bellandur with good food.
This place serves both veg & non veg.

They has the option of buffet as well as ala carte.

I tried Veg Hakka Noodles, Veg Seekh Kabab, Paneer Tikka, Veg Biryani and bubble gum milkshake.

Noodles - layered noodles along with the vegetables, those were not sticky at all
Paneer tikka - soft Paneer marinated in masala's and Cooked in Tandoor along with vegetables.
Seekh kabab - soft kabab cooked on the charcoals or tandoor
Veg Biryani - authentic Biryani, having served in layers. Layer's of rice & masala gravy.

Taste 4.5/5
Service 3.5/5
Ambiance 4/5
Value for money 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Writings the review after a couple of visits - one good thing about this restaurant has Indian, Chinese, BBQ and western(fries, sizzlers, etc...) together.
I had onion rings(ok ok), French fries(good), bbq sauce sizzlers(too sweet - not ok), veg sizzlers(ok ok), pepper chicken boneless(good), Chicken steak (good), soups(ok ok), Bombay fried rice(not great)
overall good/decent enough
taste : 3.5/5service: 2.5/5 (even no people is there - ll take little more time)ambience: 3.5/5value for the money: 4/5')]

address: 548/1, Syed Plaza, Outer Ring Road, Bellandur, Bangalore
name: @ The Bbq
cuisines: BBQ, Continental, North Indian, Chinese, Beverages
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A quite good place in bellandur with good food.
This place serves both veg & non veg.

They has the option of buffet as well as ala carte.

I tried Veg Hakka Noodles, Veg Seekh Kabab, Paneer Tikka, Veg Biryani and bubble gum milkshake.

Noodles - layered noodles along with the vegetables, those were not sticky at all
Paneer tikka - soft Paneer marinated in masala's and Cooked in Tandoor along with vegetables.
Seekh kabab - soft kabab cooked on the charcoals or tandoor
Veg Biryani - authentic Biryani, having served in layers. Layer's of rice & masala gravy.

Taste 4.5/5
Service 3.5/5
Ambiance 4/5
Value for money 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Writings the review after a couple of visits - one good thing about this restaurant has Indian, Chinese, BBQ and western(fries, sizzlers, etc...) together.
I had onion rings(ok ok), French fries(good), bbq sauce sizzlers(too sweet - not ok), veg sizzlers(ok ok), pepper chicken boneless(good), Chicken steak (good), soups(ok ok), Bombay fried rice(not great)
overall good/decent enough
taste : 3.5/5service: 2.5/5 (even no people is there - ll take little more time)ambience: 3.5/5value for the money: 4/5')]

  Thank you so much for the delicious food! I had order my lunch from here, menu is quite interesting at a reasonable price I tried - Dal bati, Missi roti and Dum aalo. This is the best Dal bati in Bangalore I have ever had. I like the extra crunchiness of it. Missi roti and Dum aalo was too good.

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ordered in from this place and their kheema biryani was authentic and tasty. Quantity was good and the food was fresh. It was authentically Hyderabadi as well. Enjoyed the spices and the flavours'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Recently ordered a Special Chicken Biryani from this restaurant. The taste was good, it has chicken kebabs with spicy gravy kept over biryani. Packing was very good. Got it with Raita, Salan and Onion salad.

thedelighttable.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is a trip one should definitely not miss. Heard good feedback from a friend about chicken keema biryani and tried it on the first opportunity. Delivered in a cute little pack and neat bowl the biryani was a good surprise. Well chopped chicken keema on top of biryani rice. Good whole garam masala taste and good raita. Definitely would try to visit the place.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This is a new place which only has delivery service and no seating space. Their menu is very simple and small with 6 types of Biryanis and kebabs. Ordered for the first time the Special Chicken Biryani from this place today and the presentation of the food was flawless.

Coming to the food, the quantity was more than sufficient and fulfilling however it was too spicy in terms of chili factor. Instead of usual chicken pieces, they served this biryani with boneless chunks which I'm fine with cause the quantity of was good.

Since I've had Biryanis from more places all across India than I can remember, this was not a total punch in terms of authenticity but it's decent than many other places that I've tried so far from here at Bangalore. I'm sure, these guys will do good by looking at what they are serving.")]

name: Dindigul Thalappakatti
cuisines: Biryani, Chinese, North Indian, South Indian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable. Although its a busy place but no one will bother you. Kudos to the staff for getting everything on time, you just need to ask them once. I ordered 2 chicken boneless biryani and it was good. It would be great to come here during the day and try out their thali once.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Went for a weekday lunch. Ordered Mutton Biryani and Pomfret. Biryani was okay, but the Fish smelled and was dry. Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is a newly opened outlet of thalappakatti in Trinity circle.. The place is quite small. But gets pretty crowded during lunch. The waiting time is a good half hour if you reach there after 1.30pm.
The service is quite fast and prompt.
We ordered lamb chops, where the mutton was well seasoned and tender, the kottu porotta was mushy and and tasted blank, we then ordered mutton and chicken boneless biriyani both tasted decently good but way too oily. There was always something missing taste wise,in all the dishes I had. The biriyani quantity is good enough to share with another person but not the starters.
I felt that the food was overly priced.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
 
Normally I end up having biriyani from selective places only but today made an exception of trying out this new place @thalappakatti near office.

This place supposedly brings in the famous Dindigul biriyani,which is a Tamil style biriyani with the short grained seeraga samba rice and has branches across the world.
But unfortunately chicken biriyani was dry, with two tiny pieces of chicken and a egg and hardly any flavor.

The black pepper chicken was nothing but fried chicken tossed in soya sauce, which was suggested to us as the must try.

Such a disappointing experience, that I'm definitely not going back.")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A small restaurant located near many PGs. The staff is friendly and courteous. Popular among bachelors living around. Do try Poha and Samosa chat! Have been here a couple of times and the quality of food is good. They have a variety of dishes on the menu. The service is quick and efficient. Better to visit this place rather than the overpriced Village Restaurant nearby. Worth a visit!!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have been to this place a lottt of times....
One of our favorite places.. If you want best north Indian food then go through it... Chicken tikka masala .. And kulcha with kamli kabab is best ...it is new in town ambience is small but food is good ?'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Extremely brilliant food ..got it home delivered.. it was as fresh as you are eating in a restaurant .
Paneer butter masala was best and rotis were rightly cooked'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I eat paneer subji and roti. It was delicious.
It had a good quantity. You can always try it. The place is small but good. Food was well served and was fresh.')]

  Was searching for nice Hyderabadi biryani. visited Kitchens@Whitefield and checked multiple options before this place

2nd - He allowed me to check small portion before ordering - Tasted authentic, properly cooked 
3rd - Showed me the packing material (250ml, 500ml, 1000ml) -  was nice and Hygienic 
With no further thoughts ordered Boneless Chicken Biryani , Leg Piece Biryani and Veg Dum Biryani for my Team. all 1000ml packs for 25 people all together. The food was ready on time for pickup. 
Food was delivered as promised. Everyone appreciated the taste (hats off Chef). will order again soon.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ordered first time from this restaurant one boneless chicken biryani. The first thing I liked about this restaurant is that the price is pocket friendly. So according to me one should definitely order biryani from this restaurant and trust me you are going to love the food. I will definitely order some different types of biryani as it is added in my favourite list. Good work from basmati's biryani nation.")]

  A small restaurant located near many PGs. The staff is friendly and courteous. Popular among bachelors living around. Do try Poha and Samosa chat! reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Having been a huge fan of the chain?s first (?) outlet in Saket, I was chomping at the bit to try it?s outlet in my city. On a sunny Sunday morning, visited here for breakfast. With wood benches on the lawn makes the outdoor section, there?s a surprisingly well-accommodating inside section as well.

We had the marinated chicken, the pulled lamb sourdough and the tasters for drinks, where we substituted nitro coffee for salted chocolate instead. A few of the drinks weren?t available but otherwise the food is great and the drinks delicious. Add to this their friendly service, and this place makes for a great visit, especially for coffee connoisseurs / enthusiasts.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I like this place quite a lot. Indoor and outdoor seating options with an amazing ambience is going to pull you to this place quite often. I had a iced mocha and an avocado sandwich. The coffee was refreshing and the avocado sandwich had an organic punch. I also wanted to have the nitrogen infused coffee but since it was out of stock I am going to visit this place again to have that for sure. Avocado sandwich was a good one to start with and having said that I would also like to explore other items in the food menu next time I visit this place. The courteous staff is worth a mention as it adds value to my experience over there.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Really like the ambience here. Coffee is obviously superb, and the food is not bad and decently priced. They have a nice selection of lunch/cafe items. I love the iced coffee, it's super smooth and not too rich, just to my taste. Special mention for the stunningly beautiful crockery - all the ceramic ware is just perfect.

Service could be a little faster, and the tables are a little too close together for my liking, but it's a great place that has potential to become my new favorite hangout spot!"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Had heard a lot about Blue Tokai and hence decided to try it myself. The place is big with both indoor and outdoor seating. The staff is extremely courteous and helpful in recommending dishes to try. We tried Mocha which was good, sweet potato wedges, Mexican bowl and grilled chicken marinated with charred peppers. They believe in serving healthy food and hence the menu is not likeable by everyone. We found the food to be quite average.

Ambience - 4
Food - 3
Service - 5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A good day begins with good breakfast . I thought of trying out this place for breakfast on Saturday morning.
This is a very beautiful home turned into cafe . Lovely place with pleasant ambiance both indoor and outdoor seating .

We ordered for Free ranged poached eggs on chefs recommendation , honestly we were disappointed with this since the bread was burnt .
I ordered for falafel flat bread . This was the best and I feel it is a must try . It is falafel with pita bread n pumpkin hummus . Was totally in love with the taste .
In addition we tried their baked sweet potato fries and it was super yummy . Just tried their cold brew coffee .

  With their diverse coffee menu Blue Tokai has finally arrived in Bengaluru. The cafÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ¨ is spacious and the decor is simply complementing.   Looks like it?s an house that has been turned into a cafe which looks lovely. The natural light right in the middle of the cafe/house makes the seating look even better. reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have admitted my mom in a reputed hospital in Jayanagar where outside food is strictly not allowed and their canteen closes by 9:30 PM. My home is in Whitefield. Almost after 1:30 hrs journey I reached the hospital by 10:00 PM. I was super hungry. Around 10:30 only I started searching for food in Zomato, I don?t want to eat heavy but want something hot and steamed. What would be a better choice than momos? So, found this Momo Blues! Ordered both momo blues oz and shrimp momos - I was totally surprised by the quality and taste of the momos. The momos were really steaming hot and soft. Even in many big restaurants, the momos I had were hard and dry! These momos tasted fresh and juicy... if you are staying in and around of Koramangala and if you are a momo lover, then your go-to place is momo blues! Their shrimp momos worth the every penny! They were perfect as well!
Thanks to Zomato?s delivery guy! He came real quick and saved me from my hunger!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues.   Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.

Excellent service and good food. Had a pleasant experience.

address: 10, Opposite Forum Mall, Taverekere, Suddagunte Palya, BTM, Bangalore
name: Fogg
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.
Greek salad - Lettuce, Olives and Feta Cheese in the perfect mix.
Vergin Fried chicken - Chicken Fried with a coated batter. Tasted good.
Mix sause pasta - Penne Rigate Pasta with chicken cubes in a mixed sauce.
3 cheese pesto pizza - Generous servings of Cheddar, Parmesan and Mozarella Cheese layered on the Thin crust Pizza base tasted really well. You could feel the Cheese in every bite.
Chicken wrap - Chicken Cubes with veggies wrapped in Arabian Bread.
Chicken Nachos - Julienned chicken pieces and cheesw spread on Crisp Nachos.
Chicken pot rice - Jasmine rice with a mild Green Curry Gravy with veggies. Very flavourful and tasty.
Prawns kudla de Fogg - A preparation similar to the Prawns Ghee Roast with a similar texture and taste.
Excellent service and good food. Had a pleasant experience.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ambience is very good
Hooka is amazing specially Fogg hooka special.
Food is good. Pasta specially. Must try place.
Good music with live videos.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Terribly expensive with extremely small portions on the starters. But the brews are absolutely stunning and knock outs. That and the killer terrace ambiance deserves this 4 star rating.
I had the wit and the Weiss and they were easily the best I?ve had in a while. The customary chilli chicken starter was excellent but the quantity was too little like stated before.

Go for their brews. You?ll love em.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  What a wonderful place!!! 5 stars is very much deserved!!! Beautiful ambience!!! Tasty food and kick-ass beers!!! Over-all a lovely evening!!! Order anything there it's all lip smaking!!! Beer is the high light!!! Service is really amazing!!! Kudos guys u set up standards and bench mark for south Bangalore breweries and kitchen!!!! Will not hesitate to visit often!!!!perfect family evening dinner"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Perfect place for weekend lunch... I?m sure it looks beautiful in the evenings too though looking at the other pics but the open dining area is very spacious and just apt for a meal outside.. the food is amazing, friendly staff, valet parking available, great spot to click some nice pics, lovely ambience.. definitely recommend it..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls. 
Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.
 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

  Loved the experience at Levitate bar. Food was really good and they have a good ambience as well. Courteous staff. Coming to the starters we loved the rava upma cheese balls and jalapeno cheese balls along with the Vietnamese Loaded Fries and Tandoori Bharwan mushrooms. Broccoli 65 was well made. Chicken Tikka, Tempura prawns and tandoori prawns tasted so good. And in the main course we tried the Farmers Grilled veggies pizza and Thai red curry which were delicious!!   So, it was the new year's Eve and we were expecting to spend a nice evening with music drinks and dinner.

The ambience is super cool... Beautiful and refreshing. The open terrace seating at 2 levels is quite spacious and beautifully decorated. The live music being played just enhanced the whole experience.

  Read about this new brewery through Zomato and social media apps and gave it a try on Christmas evening . On the whole it?s a good place . Starting with the positives , their ambience has to be their biggest plus point , lovely simple roof top with lot of space . The few negatives to be pointed out can be their service which is very slow and can definitely get better and also the attitude of some of the staff can surely be more courteous towards customers. But this being a new place , would surely get better I hope . On the whole a definite must try .'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Another pub!! Another brewery!! Man JP nagar is upgrading for sure... One good place to hang out this one. Been there on Christmas eve and found a pretty decent crowd considering it was a Monday. There was a detailed live performance which was very entertaining.

Coming to the beer, I tasted only the wheat beer and liked it. Cant say bad, at the same time cant say very good. The food is good, their presentation is slightly off the hook. They serve a few dishes in large coffee cups which makes the quantity look less. I found it to be ok and not that bad. It can of course be better.

I hold back one star because I noticed that the waiter dropped a cup filled with dip accidentally. This was right next to our table and the same was not cleared. It was there till the time we left. This is something the management has to look into.

address: 4th B Cross, Koramangala 5th Block, Bangalore
name: Biergarten
dish_liked: Beer, Mezze Platter, Penne Arrabiata Pasta, Cocktails, Bruschettas, Peri Peri Chicken, Pizza
cuisines: Continental, North Indian, Chinese, European, BBQ, Finger Food, Asian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Well, the place has a charm. It's nice, chic and classy.
Very well behaved attenders, and a warm and cozy ambience. The IPA striked the mark, and the food tasted great too. Prawns were awesome and absolutely loved the pizza. The place offers a sweet experience."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Totally loved this place.. quite huge and food was delicious ? and ambience is amazing and more over nice management,everything was super fresh and yummy. Probably this place is gonna be my next Sunday adda too ??'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Biergarten located at kormangala vis one of the best brewery in the neighborhood right next to truffles.

Ambience :- Ambience is something you expect always along with the good food. With total exposure of outer environment where you will get the cool breeze of Bangalore. They have a perfect ambience to be there with someone special. You can plan your date here with your special one's.

They have there some of the good beers available like viena lager was one of the best I loved. Other than beers they also have good option for cocktails.

Service:- Though the place is too big the service is prompt and staff is courteous.

What all we had :-

Ragada patties 5/5

Fish kurkure 5/5

Tandoori Momo 4/5

Assorted kulcha platter 5/5

Bheja fry 4/5

Main course :-

Tangadi chicken 5/5

Pan fried noodles 5/5

Hyderabadi chicken biryani 5/5

Alfredo pasta 4/5

Deserts :-

Jaggery mouse cake 4/5

Trio of kulfi 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We went there on a Sunday afternoon. It?s a rooftop place so it was quite airy . . I am sure this will be a great place to hang out during evenings . Food was good . We ordered Veg Thai Red Curry , Crispy Mushroom Bao and Diavola Pizza . For desserts we ordered Churros .'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Hello Fellas,
Finally visited this beauty!!
Much waited place and a great Brewry open Their doors.

Ambience: wow!! Such a great interiors, with selected lamp shades and lovely set of bar.

Beverages: I am not a beer drinker but this place made we try their mouthwatering beers and some great Classic Gin and Tonic.
My friend though tried some Excellent presented cocktails.

Food: Such a handful sort of menu, tried their Ghee roast prawns, crispy chilli Pork. Pandi curry , tequila chicken and what not.

Service: I would like to write about the service as we were Seating at bar and the service we got was just wow!! Thanks for Samuel and Sunil who guided us and made us comfortable as home and tried their recommended food paired with great alcohol.

I would like to recommend this place to all the age group.
Thanks to team biergarten for lovely experience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

address: 104, Vijay Jatti Building, Industrial Area, Koramangala 5th Block, Bangalore
name: Ulavacharu
dish_liked: Ulavacharu, Biryani, Bangla Kodi, Rajugari Kodi Pulao, Curd Rice, Gadwal Kodi Pulao, Plain Rice
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had been yesterday to this amazing place with friends over lunch.. They had the food served in banana leaf for the 1st time since it opened. We ordered Konaseema Kodi Vepudu and Bamboo Chicken as non veg starters and Mokkajoanna Vepudu (Baby Corn dish) as veg starter.. The bamboo chicken was spicy to the likes of everyone. Distinct bamboo flavour takes the dish to different level.. For mains, we took Ulavacharu Kodi pulao, Dal fry, rotis and Veg salad.. They were very good..

I would highly recommend this place to all if they want to try Authentic Andhra food..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Last week visited Ulavacharu with my friends. Food taste and quality were pretty decent except desserts.

Service was not impressive. We asked them politely to wait for serving until we finish but they were in urgency to serve food.

Ambience is quite different and good.

Ratings:
Food: 4/5
Quality: 4/5
Service:3/5
Ambience: 3.5/5'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  A typical Andhra reasturant like all the other reasturant, the ambience is not that great , it's got a raw feel, but doens't seem exciting , the food was like any other Andhra reasturant , nothing different. The customer service is pretty average, pricing is way too high.. it's like any other Andhra reasturant.."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I need to explore this place more. My first experience was not so great. We ordered Raju kodi biryani. Rice was sticky, there were rice lumps and pieces were hard and bland.
Got it replaced with Mutton biryani and it was just normal biryani.
I would say its on the pricy side atleast by 50 bucks.
Ambience is rustic and reminds of rural set up and Granny's house.
I somehow feel they are really good at what they are preparing, i just need to explore more or go at the right time."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  What a brilliant place \U0001f929 let's get straight to the food. I had Telangana mamsam Kura and kulcha. It was like a marriage made in heaven. The mutton was brilliantly cooked, the gravy was so flavourful. I cannot stop gushing about how brilliant it was. A little bit too oily, no doubt. But it hit all the right notes!

I also tried the uluvacharu Kodi pulao.. the biriyani was definitely good but nothing extraordinary. Definitely going back there for more!

A small feedback would be to also explain the various dishes that you have since the entire menu has the Telugu names. It would be easier for the customers to understand what they're ordering."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It was my first time visit to the place and trust me I was awestruck with the entrance and then with the interior but the food was as tasty as the entrance and the stuff being so polite and asking for your comfort zone and making you explain the food items as the menu for the north indian to understand is difficult. The way the atmosphere they have maintained is beautiful and the Manager. Suresh was excellent at the service he suggested us the best spicy biryani - Gadwal Kodi Pulao and we ordered it and damn yummmmmy!! Infact I took one parcel to send to my city surat,gujarat with a friend next day and it still dint get spoilt. However we ordered three parcel but they were out of stock :( so had to send just one. But beautiful experience and not too pricy. Thank you for everything!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Koramangala has new destination for another Authentic cusine and its Ualavacharu. Its opened in the prime location and easy to find. Their Ambience is mind blowing. Starting from the entrance to every corner the decoration is very well pictured. They are 2 branches in Hyderabad and this is their 1st branch in Bangalore.

Coming to food, I loved Raju gari kodi pulav- which was little gravish, spicy and is different from any other biryanis.

For starters we ordered Kona seema kodi vepudu- which is semi gravy and fiery. Chapala Vepudu was crispy and good.

Main course we took Roti along Andhra Kodi curry which was spicy and had fine taste. Gadwal Kodi pulao was good in taste. Apricot Delight desert is a must try.

All the food are spicy and this would an irresistible place for Andhra cuisine lovers. Will definitely mark this place for Andhra meal next time. Worth trying. !'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Another badly wanted to go restaurant with lot of expectations. It was a Saturday evening and this was a new place in town. The interiors of this place is very good and we were pretty impressed with the variety of pulao/biryani options we could see on the menu.

We did ordered almost three different pulao and starters. The Andra style starters were good to start with and than comes the biryani. The presentation of the biryani was good but the biryani?s were not up-to the badge. What started with good experience ended with a satisfactory note.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu is the new Andhra speciality restaurant which has recently opened up in Kormangala,Bangalore.
The decor is done beautifully with Lord Krishna idol,stone pillars,wooden waterfall structure and a whole lot of comfortable seatings.
Being a south Indian I absolutely love Andhra flavours which is spicy and laced with richness of ghee.just the way I like it ?
I personally loved the Ulvacharu,Bangla Kodi,Konaseema Kodi Vepudu,Raju Gari Kodi Pulav.
Do visit this legendary place which is famous in Hyderabad and now serving delicacies in Bengaluru?

thegalwhoblogs.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ulavacharu the restuarant which brings the finest delicacies of andhra prsdesh to our own Koramangala.

Ulavacharu itself a dish prepared from horse grame which is very famous in Andhra Pradesh.

Rustic Ambience which gives you the feel of old homes in village.

Welcoming Indian desserts were
Khaja and badusha.

Bangla Kodi a uniquely prepared dish where boneless chicken stuffed in a potato pockets.

The food was amazing especially Raju Gari kodi pulao.

And Kona Seema Kodi vepudu this was the spiciest chicken Starter I had here.

The gutti vankaya pulao this was amazing.

Tandoori fish don't miss out this guy's it's a must have here.A full size koramenu cooked with right amount of masala.

Apricot delight a very popular sweet dish of Hyderabad made with apricot and served with cream.
This was a bliss as always desserts are love."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  After a long and successful stint at Hyderabad, the birthplace of Andhra Cuisine, this restaurant now serves Bangaloreans with the same awesome cuisine that Hyderabadis have enjoyed for sometime.
The dishes here are prepared quite well and taste good.

Raju Gari kodi palav is one of its kind, it was flavourful, kind of semi gravy, tasted really good. name: Le Arabia
dish_liked: Chicken Biryani
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The quantity is more than enough, but the price does not quantify the quality. The rice was undercooked, so flavourless. Need to improve the taste and quality for sure'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

name: Bob's Bar
dish_liked: Murgh Ghee Roast, Beer
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We recently visited the Koramangala outlet of Bob?s Bar and frankly speaking we were quite impressed. Both food and drinks are very reasonably priced. Service is prompt, they have kept the dÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ©cor simple but classy. The best part is they have half portions for most of the food items which means you can try more items from the menu. We tried Mascarenas beef roast, Chicken ghee roast & Malnad pork. All three were pretty good but being a pork fan I liked the malnad pork the most.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Koramangala just got its new watering hole that too at dirt cheap rates. From the same house as that of Byg Brewski but really reasonable. What I loved about the place is the availability of half portions. My recommendations are Mascarenas beef roast, Chicken ghee roast & Malnad pork.. the delicious food were accompanied by some white rum, gin & scotch. Service was prompt but they should stock more variety of alcohol.. lot of them were unavailable when we went. Will visit again!!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The latest addition in Koramangala and so happy to be able to walk up and enjoy a beer and short eats without dreading the traffic

We had yummy military style Liver masala
Kheema dosa
Malnad pork
Gowda mutton chops
Fluffy Kerala parota with some kebabs
Everything was cooked to perfection

The whole place looks so nice and the high light is the painting on one of the walls , especially for us old Bangaloreans as we kept spotting the other iconic spots of old Bangalore most of them only memories now
Anila our waitress was very sweet and courteous and served us with s smile

We also had their take of apple pie and a nice cooffe cheese cake

We washed it down with some beer and after ages had some spiced rum and coke

Looks like this is going to be our favourite spot to hang out ??'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Not every often I give out 5 stars to a place but this place deserves every bit of it!
Located in Koramangala 7th main, diagonally opposite to Fenny's, this is a place for one and all.

Ambience: 4/5
It has sort of an indoor and outdoor seating arrangements. Gives the look of a cafe, comfortable and cozy.

Staff: 5/5
Extremely courteous. Prompt service. You'd happily pay the extra service charge added in the bill.

Price: 6/5
Now this is something which is absolutely UNBELIEVABLE!
The food and the booze both are priced almost at half the rates than the other place.
They serve Jack Daniels Fire at 195!
Glenfiddich at 200ish!
Same is the case with food.

Food: 4/5
Aunthentic Desi spices and taste.
If you're looking for a place which serves nachos and fries, this isn't the place for you!

Things we tried: 6-8 Beer, Pork chilly, beef chilly, Peanut masala, Naked Anjal fish fry, Grilled prawns!

And guess our bill?
2000 bucks!

Try out this place to believe it!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

foodforlife24x7.blogspot.com"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened restaurant which deals with your craving for dal makhni. A dhaba but in an uptown style. The service is a bit slow, but the food and the kebabs are yummm. Also, the green chutney is worth licking your fingers. Nice place for a fam jam!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Newly opened in JP Nagar, this place is close to RV Dental college. We went on a lazy afternoon to check out this place. The ambience of this place is very nice, with decent staff ready to offer good service. Coming to food, the menu is simple yet good. From their lassi to their thali, everything is authentic Punjabi style.
Overall, would recommend you to try this place once. A good place to have decent food.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Baba Chatkora is one of the options in JP Nagar for rejoicing authentic North Indian delicacies.

Visited this place only on the second day of after they opened. The place is nicely done. Bollywood and Punjabi numbers played at the backdrop gives a nice vibe to the place.

The food was decent.
We ordered Matka Lassi, Dhabha style Paneer, Ghobi matar and Butter naan.
Expected more from the Dhabha style paneer but it was the same as you would get in any any other North Indian restaurant.
The Matka Lassi was really thick and tasted great but the portion was pretty small.

A decent option for family dining but a bit overpriced. When you have so many options nearby and when a customer is looking for places which offers great value for money or something exemplary, Baba Chatkora fails miserably on that regard.

Happy eating!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Yay! Baba Chatkora is in JP Nagar now. Everything about this place is splendid. The food, the ambiance, the friendly staff and of course the music.

We ordered:
Soya Chaaps
Kulcha
And paneer starters
Plus they have the winter special menu too, and the gajar ka halwa is en pointe!

If you are craving for North Indian delicacies, look no further.')]

  This place was beautiful and spacious. You will not be able to find such huge places in kormangla to even shake a leg. But this one was beautiful with pretty interiors and soothing atmosphere.   This is such an amazing place in the heart of Bangalore! The decor is amazing, from the design to the furniture to the execution, it is all perfect!
I went there with Hitesh Asopa for dinner the other night and we ordered a Khao Suey for him, and Paneer Anardana with Butter Garlic Naan for me.
First of all, the plating was awesome!
The staff is really courteous and soft spoken. I asked them if the sabzi was cooked in oil and the chef came and assured me that it's ghee that they cook their sabzis in. That was too kind of him.
The taste was out of the world! Both the dishes were just perfect. Burmese Khao Suey was full of flavors and it was aromatic. We felt the freshness in each bite.
I would loooove to visit again soon to try the other dishes!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I love love love this place. My first experience here was amazing. I went on a Thursday to meet a friend and we absolutely enjoyed everything about this place.

Ambience is so well placed, lit, and taken care of. I like the intricate details.
The staff are extending friendly and well mannered.
The beer of course is fantastic and my love for freshly brewed beer only bolstered.

Food- bacon pizza and prawns wrapped in bacon. Yum yum yum.

Had a flat liner shot to wrap up the evening and that was made well too!

This place is definitely going on top of my list of places in Koramangala. ??'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  Very rarely do we find places that tick all the boxes of your dining experience. Biergarten was one place that had it all. Situated inside a building in Koramangala, the restaurant is massive and the decor allows free open spaces, bringing in lots of light and creating an ideal space for lunches, evenings out and dinners. The staff is exceedingly polite and courteous and cater to your every need. Starting off with the iced coffee, the drink was done to perfection and the fresh whipped cream was excellent. The nachos frankly weren't much to rave about, but the chicken bao was absolutely succulent and filled with flavour, as was the vodka infused chicken tangdi, with delectable flavours. The kahlua mousse ended a great meal, the mousse was done well, but could have had more depth in terms of its flavour, and it makes you feel rather bloated. On the whole, Biergaten served up was an experience that I would love to re live again, sampling a wider variety of dishes, next time around."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very quick and prompt service and excellent food. Totally coming back here.
Nachos, Mushroom bites - the portions weren't small. Good enough to fill one up.
The Bailey's cheesecake bowled me over!

littlefoodiegirl.com"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ambience is amazing, decor is pretty and service was on point for most of the time.

We ordered veg assorted kulchas and fish tikka for starters. They both were amazing. The dips with kulchas were delicious and complemented well. There were different stuffings for kulcha.
For mains, we ordered sun dried tomato and feta pizza which was delicious. We also ordered Khao suey. We found it a little sweeter than expected.

For beverages we had better bitter and long Island iced tea for cocktails which were pretty good. In mocktails we went for litchi twist and summer punch. Litchi twist was delicious while summer punch was very ordinary.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED

  Visited this place on friday night for a corporate party.
* Ambience was nice with open terrace and plants everywhere . Big and spacious.
* In food few items were really good and few were average. Ghee roast prawn and chicken , panner chilly and tandoori fish were really good. Nachos and few veg dishes were average.
* In Drinks , we had brew beers which were fine. Mocktails were also good.
* In Dessert they dont have much options .

  We ordered the Greek Salad, Veg Nachos and the Nalli ka salan.

The nachos lived up to its name (being one of the most popular dishes here) and the Nalli ka salan was exquisite. The latter was cooked to perfection with the meat falling off the bone. The Greek salad was great too but was shadowed by the nachos and the Nalli ka Salan. We also ordered the Golden ale which was good.

Overall, I would definitely recommend this place to someone who would want to enjoy good food and alcohol at a lively place. The service was great too (shoutout to Mr. Rakesh)


whinendine.com'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambience when you enter the 2nd floor. Just besides to truffles. They have 2 floor seating. Talking about food and drinks.. Tried veg lasagna, nachos and pizza all were decent and portion served was fulfilling, service was quick on monday evening. Drinks are also worth a try. They served complimentary cake as well for the occasion we visited. Bonus point is zomato gold on food.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Another brewery in Koramangala!

Very close to JNC road, next to truffles. Quite a big entrance with waiting area. They got a very spacious dinning area, with nice music.

Brew: I would rate 5/5, outstanding!

Food: We started with,

1. Guishao Chilly Chicken, cooked in a Chinese style with a taste of sweet and spicy.

2. Tequila chicken tangri kebab, served with curd dip

3. BBQ smoked chicken pesto pizza

They accept zomato gold on food ?

Overall, its a nice place to try brewed beer and yes of course, to try all the dishes. We had a happy friyay dinning. Service is super fast and prompt. Will visit again soon. :)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  Difficult to find this place as the entrance is overshadowed by huge board of Truffles. Once u enter, u feel like u just got the secret door to Narnia.
Their seasonal beers are too good. However their Vienna beer is big let down. It killed my buzz. Suprisingly!!!!!.
They have the best Nachos in town. Its spicy, crisy and tangy.
Definitely going back this wknd. Now brooks and bonds have tough competition'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Good brewery, with a great rooftop area that served some tap beers! We ordered the litre beers and had the golden ale and the IPA, the latter disappointed a little, because the basis of which we ordered it was the description on the menu and I tasted no fruit! We also had the Khao suey, which was tasty and just as I like it! We also had the sausage dish with bacon, I was a fan but the slaw they served with it was average!
All nitpicking, but don't want to take away the shine from a good place!
Worth a visit, Cheers!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Starting off with the ambience!
It's pleasant lively!
Loved the greenery and the welcome!
The staff is very polite. Great music.
Each dish is worth the price
The quantity of the dishes are good a amount.
The food tastes yum.
Had a really good time, will surely visit again!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  As you enter the hotel like lobby, you can feel that it's a lovely place to be. However, the hostess said there wasn't any place and we went up to find half the place empty. They said it was reserved, however we did get seating when we said we were only there for 30 minutes. An hour later tables were still available, so reservation/space management needs to be improved. The drinks are very reasonably priced for a prime location in koramangala with such beautiful visual ambience. The music gets annoyingly loud though, so if you want to have a conversation, finish it in the lobby. The food is pretty good too, but service is so slow, they took 20 minutes to bring me a whiskey. I'd visit again and reconsider upgrading this to a 4 if the experience is better, so do try it."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Overall Rating: 5/5

Food: 5/5
Quality and Quantity were up to the mark.
We ordered VegNachos, SoyaChaap, Pasta(Red and White Sauce), Pizza (Veg and Paneer). All of them were good in taste.

Service: 5/5
Staff were attentive. Infact, he helped us to choose the Veg menu and explained about the portion of the food we were going to order. I liked it.

Ambience: 5/5
I wish I could mention more than 5. Ambience is just amazing that to explore this place you cannot judge in one visit. The background music, seating arrangement, space between 2 seating space, etc is taken care very nicely. The place is not at all crowded (in positive way) in terms of arrange.

Verdict: Well, this place is very beautifully and well maintained. You can visit this place anytime to spend some time with your Parents / Spouse / Siblings / Friends.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Awesome experience, just loved my visit here yesterday.

Ambience was on spot. Music, lighting, sitting arrangement and the general vibe on rooftop is just perfect.

Service was quick, responsive and very good.

Food was in sync with ambience, we ordered soya chaap, nachos, penne arrabiata and penne white cream cheese pasta, Indiana pizza and mushroom pizza.

Loved it very much overall. Will visit soon to try other options in veg. Plus point is Zomato gold which is like the cherry on a cake top. ?'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing food, kick-ass ambience, fast service, this place has all of it. Their nachos are out of this world while penne arrabiata pasta is amazing. Other things that I tried and loved them were soya chaap, diavola pizza, Indiana pizza and penne creamy cheese pizza. Their garlic bread is also much better than what most places serve. Definitely worth visiting. Plus this place is huge so getting a table should not be an issue at all.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Visited this place on Sunday noon. So glad that there wasn't any queues and tables were readily available.

A lot of tables over few floors were shown to us. They had a very well decorated bar counter at the center and the whole place is very well lit up.

The Canadian putine fries we had was amazing! First dish I've had where they mixed fried and crushed olives! It was new and delicious.

The pork belly was well cooked and marinated, although could've used more mushroom gravy sause.
The pizza was good as well, the sun dried tomatoes were too hard.

Loved the fruit punch!

Great lunch. Would recommend!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED

name: Levitate Brewery and Kitchen

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Terribly expensive with extremely small portions on the starters. But the brews are absolutely stunning and knock outs. That and the killer terrace ambiance deserves this 4 star rating.
I had the wit and the Weiss and they were easily the best IÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ve had in a while. The customary chilli chicken starter was excellent but the quantity was too little like stated before.

Go for their brews. YouÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ll love em.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  What a wonderful place!!! 5 stars is very much deserved!!! Beautiful ambience!!! Tasty food and kick-ass beers!!! Over-all a lovely evening!!! Order anything there it's all lip smaking!!! Will not hesitate to visit often!!!!perfect family evening dinner"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Perfect place for weekend lunch... IÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92m sure it looks beautiful in the evenings too though looking at the other pics but the open dining area is very spacious and just apt for a meal outside.. the food is amazing, friendly staff, valet parking available, great spot to click some nice pics, lovely ambience.. definitely recommend it..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls. 
Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.
 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

Some dishes tried here was -

  The place is good and the ambience is perfect to hangout with friends and family.
The service can be improved and can be quick as well, we actually had to remind the waiters for our order.
But overall good experience and the variety of Craft Beer you get makes it perfect.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Loved the experience at Levitate bar. Food was really good and they have a good ambience as well. Courteous staff. Coming to the starters we loved the rava upma cheese balls and jalapeno cheese balls along with the Vietnamese Loaded Fries and Tandoori Bharwan mushrooms. Broccoli 65 was well made. Chicken Tikka, Tempura prawns and tandoori prawns tasted so good. And in the main course we tried the Farmers Grilled veggies pizza and Thai red curry which were delicious!! They do have some great desserts like New York cheese cake and molten brownie which were both delicious. Definitely going back here for more!!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Pretty big and spacious place with a fairly good ambience. The service can be better, it took them quite a long time just to get one cocktail and one beer. Food is decent with good presentations. Would definitely want to visit again.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Just a hop-skip away from Vega city, this place is all that you'd look for in a watering hole. With the brewery scene heating up around JP Nagar, Levitate is surely going to be "the" place to watch-out. Pretty ambiance, wonderful atmosphere all year long (what with a mini-forest right outside!), and easy connectivity could make it a preferred choice. Didn't try too many dishes, but the nachos were quite tasty. Service was quick and prompt too. Would love to go back here to test the "kitchen" part!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Latest addition to South Bangalore this another great place with lovely ambiance. Seating is spread across multiple levels and the roof top provides a great view of the mini forest and ideal for late afternoon and evenings. Beers are perfect German craft with some yummy food to pair with. Service is attentive and quick. Great place to try be it will friends, co workers or family!'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I fell in love with this place. It's situated in the heart of JP Nagar. Really loved the ambience, the food and also the drinks. The staff were amazing, and the service was good as well."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Another addition to JP NagarÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s brewery list: Levitate Brewery and Kitchen. Walkable from Vega city Mall on Bannerghatta Road, this newly opened brewery is all set to compete with Brewsky and others in the same locality. You will definitely love the ambience of this place. Courteous staff is another thing that will stay in your memory after visiting this place. Coming to food, everything tasted good except pizzas. The base was hard and the toppings were stale. Hope the management takes this feedback and works towards improvement.

  So, it was the new year's Eve and we were expecting to spend a nice evening with music drinks and dinner.
And yes.. Levitate was a perfect place for it.
The ambience is super cool... Beautiful and refreshing. The open terrace seating at 2 levels is quite spacious and beautifully decorated. The live music being played just enhanced the whole experience.
Secondly the food is great. I could write about the Continental food... Pizza, pasta, burger, cheese balls etc. And it was delicious.
Drinks are quite decent too... The home beer is quite good along with other cocktails.
It's a must visit if you want to spend a nice and intimate evening overlooking the night scene."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  A new kid on the block..First of all a great location opp Mini forest. Superb Ambience specially on the rooftop floor. Decent music and good range of in-house beers.. 
Amazing gamut of food on the menu, quality stuff, quantity can be little better though. Few of the beers on the menu were not available. Initially they refused to serve our single malt order on the bar and told us that it'll be served only on 2nd floor, which was beyond our understanding. To our surprise on insisting he poured from a bottle which was kept with him only. 

We visited last saturday and looked like the mgt was overwhelmed with the turnout. I am giving the benefit of doubt as it's a very new joint so I hope the mgt takes the service as an urgent priority and fixes it asap.   The place is quite big and nice. Very good interiors pleasant ambiance. Music on the groove is great. Bar of this place look pretty cool. Now coming to the food.   Love the concept? Food presentation is awesome. Good place to hangout- another brewery to list. Their beer is good and worth trying all their samples. reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We recently visited the Koramangala outlet of BobÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s Bar and frankly speaking we were quite impressed. Both food and drinks are very reasonably priced. Service is prompt, they have kept the dÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ©cor simple but classy. The best part is they have half portions for most of the food items which means you can try more items from the menu. We tried Mascarenas beef roast, Chicken ghee roast & Malnad pork. All three were pretty good but being a pork fan I liked the malnad pork the most.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Koramangala just got its new watering hole that too at dirt cheap rates. From the same house as that of Byg Brewski but really reasonable. What I loved about the place is the availability of half portions. My recommendations are Mascarenas beef roast, Chicken ghee roast & Malnad pork.. the delicious food were accompanied by some white rum, gin & scotch. Service was prompt but they should stock more variety of alcohol.. lot of them were unavailable when we went. Will visit again!!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The latest addition in Koramangala and so happy to be able to walk up and enjoy a beer and short eats without dreading the traffic

We had yummy military style Liver masala
Kheema dosa
Malnad pork
Gowda mutton chops
Fluffy Kerala parota with some kebabs
Everything was cooked to perfection

The whole place looks so nice and the high light is the painting on one of the walls , especially for us old Bangaloreans as we kept spotting the other iconic spots of old Bangalore most of them only memories now
Anila our waitress was very sweet and courteous and served us with s smile

We also had their take of apple pie and a nice cooffe cheese cake

We washed it down with some beer and after ages had some spiced rum and coke

Looks like this is going to be our favourite spot to hang out ??'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Not every often I give out 5 stars to a place but this place deserves every bit of it!
Located in Koramangala 7th main, diagonally opposite to Fenny's, this is a place for one and all.

Ambience: 4/5
It has sort of an indoor and outdoor seating arrangements. Gives the look of a cafe, comfortable and cozy.

Staff: 5/5
Extremely courteous. Prompt service. You'd happily pay the extra service charge added in the bill.

Price: 6/5
Now this is something which is absolutely UNBELIEVABLE!
The food and the booze both are priced almost at half the rates than the other place.
They serve Jack Daniels Fire at 195!
Glenfiddich at 200ish!
Same is the case with food.

Food: 4/5
Aunthentic Desi spices and taste.
If you're looking for a place which serves nachos and fries, this isn't the place for you!

Things we tried: 6-8 Beer, Pork chilly, beef chilly, Peanut masala, Naked Anjal fish fry, Grilled prawns!

And guess our bill?
2000 bucks!

Try out this place to believe it!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

foodforlife24x7.blogspot.com"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The ambiance is very interesting.....have a view of one of the busiest roads in Koramangala, yet feel like you are away from the hustle bustle of the city. The food is decent....the fish, and beef were nice and proved to be good starters. The chicken ghee roast was a particularly good dish, but the helping was a tad small. Apart from that, it's a decent place to hang out with friends if you want to have a laid back Friday/Saturday evening."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

Normally I end up having biriyani from selective places only but today made an exception of trying out this new place @thalappakatti near office.

This place supposedly brings in the famous Dindigul biriyani,which is a Tamil style biriyani with the short grained seeraga samba rice and has branches across the world.

The black pepper chicken was nothing but fried chicken tossed in soya sauce, which was suggested to us as the must try.

Such a disappointing experience, that I'm definitely not going back.")]
