address: 18, Ramashree Arcade, MG Road, Bangalore
name: Dindigul Thalappakatti
cuisines: Biryani, Chinese, North Indian, South Indian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable. Although its a busy place but no one will bother you. Kudos to the staff for getting everything on time, you just need to ask them once. I ordered 2 chicken boneless biryani and it was good. It would be great to come here during the day and try out their thali once.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Went for a weekday lunch. Ordered Mutton Biryani and Pomfret. Biryani was okay, but the Fish smelled and was dry. Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
 
Normally I end up having biriyani from selective places only but today made an exception of trying out this new place @thalappakatti near office.

This place supposedly brings in the famous Dindigul biriyani,which is a Tamil style biriyani with the short grained seeraga samba rice and has branches across the world.
But unfortunately chicken biriyani was dry, with two tiny pieces of chicken and a egg and hardly any flavor.

The black pepper chicken was nothing but fried chicken tossed in soya sauce, which was suggested to us as the must try.

Such a disappointing experience, that I'm definitely not going back.")]

Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
 
Normally I end up having biriyani from selective places only but today made an exception of trying out this new place @thalappakatti near office.

This place supposedly brings in the famous Dindigul biriyani,which is a Tamil style biriyani with the short grained seeraga samba rice and has branches across the world.
But unfortunately chicken biriyani was dry, with two tiny pieces of chicken and a egg and hardly any flavor.

The black pepper chicken was nothing but fried chicken tossed in soya sauce, which was suggested to us as the must try.

Such a disappointing experience, that I'm definitely not going back.")]

  A pretty cafe with delicious food. The ambience is incredible, limited tables and clean. We tried multiple dishes - Dahi Chaat, Guntur Idli, Beet and Poached Pear salad, Sarson Ka Saag Sizzler, Neer Dosa and Coconut Trifle - all of them were fantastic. Extremely fast service. Definitely coming back again to try the remaining dishes.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Such a great place to sit! It's a boutique to shop and eat good food with hardly 7 tables but very well done. Their food is abviously awesome. We tried thaalipeeth and the buddha bowl was suprisingly good. How did they manage to make the millets so tasty! Loved the Khus sharbat too :)"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Glad we found this Cafe.
We had ordered Assam chai, Guntur idli, Pav platter and Cucumber chhaas. Everything was delicious.
Cucumber chhaas had mild but good flavor of cucumber and was delicious.
Guntur idli was amazingly fluffy, light and tasty.
Pav platter: loaded with flavours, but had sweet chutney inside which wasn't overpowering. I didn't mind the sweetness but my husband did. So if you mind that, you may ask then to skip the sweet chutney(saunth)
Chai: I love a good cup of tea. This was very well prepared and properly cooked. CONTENT.
Will definitely be coming back a lot here :D"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

name: Gavran Misal
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have had misal pav at Mahabaleshwar, Mumbai and various places in Goa. This is the 2nd best misal I have had till date , the misal gravy tastes amazing and the red gravy adds to the spice and sourness which makes the misal taste even better.

This place is a must try for all misal lovers in Bangalore. I would like to see other various bhaajis if possible (patal, chanyachi bhaji, sukhi bhaji etc).

Food - 4.75/5
Price- 4.5/5'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing Misal. So far a best place for Misal Pav in Bangalore. Kitchen is neat and clean. Ambiance and location of this place is good. Show runner, Sujit dada is a talkative and interesting person. I love this place for its simplicity and authentic taste. The red chutney, Ek number, A1. Must visit place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

address: 560/9, 24th Main, 7th Cross, Agara, Sector 1, HSR, Bangalore
name: Rasana
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Awesome experience in matters of food.. Being a bong in bangalore, there r cravings for bengali food,but thinking of the price we had to keep postponing it.. Bt now this place has got some delicious bengal delicacies at surprising price(pocket friendly).. Tried moglai paratha, chicken roll, fulka and chicken curry. Also ordered for my family get together. Each dish was worth a compliment... Not much photos are there as were mesmerized by the taste of the dishes that we forgot to click?? one request to start home delivery soon...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I visited this place for normal team lunch. The foods are awesomely tasty. The taste is of Bengal. Being a Bengali, it's the first restaurant in Bangalore, I found to have the regular Bengal taste in foods. Even though it's indoor seating, the place is small yet it can accommodate 16-20 people at a time.
If u r visiting this place, then mixed veg and chilly fish is a must try. The tawa rooti is same as the Bengal homemade rooti.
If u wanna taste Kolkata 's Mughlai paratha then visit in the evenings.
I am looking forward to place order for home delivery,soon."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened Bengali food joint. I found it suddenly. Initially seeing the humble and simplistic interior we were a bit reluctant to go inside. But though of giving it a try. So ordered moglai paratha and chicken role. Believe me guys, it was the best Kolkata style Moglai paratha I ever have tasted in Bangalore. The chicken kathi role was equally good. We visited a couple of more times and tried different dishes like Chicken bharta, Chicken Butter Masala, Chicken Korma, Chilli Chicken, Fish Manchurian etc. I must say that all of these items were extremely tasty and the price was very reasonable. A must try for everyone who are looking for great tasty Bengali food without worrying about the price. And not looking for swanky places.')]

address: 38, Sarjapur Main Road, Jakkasandra Extension, HSR, Bangalore
name: Hammered
dish_liked: Cocktails, Andhra Chilli Chicken, Bruschettas, Nachos, Beer, Pizza, Ravioli
cuisines: North Indian, South Indian, Continental, Asian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place on sunday evening..
*Ambience is nice , big and spacious.
*Coming to food , we ordered many dishes loaded french fries , chicken tikka , chicken golgappa and sliders burgers. Food was good.
*Drinks - we ordered LlIT and beer , very few beers were available , thats was disappointing. LIIT was good.
*MUSIC was average , they need to work on their music.
* Staff were polite and helpful.
Overall 3.5 star'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It's newly opened in hsr layout. The place is huge . Indoor seating is basically in a huge hall nicely transformed into a place for dining. A huge balcony for outdoor seating. However , we ordered a hukkah just to find out they ran out of coal at 6 in evening. Also had bad experiences with the billing as we had few discount vouchers and there policies were little twisted with that.Our experience in other outlets have been better I'd say."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  We had called to ask about the availabilty of draught beer. They said its available and we reached the place now they say they dont have it.

The fries and nachos are not homemade so nothing special about it, chilli chicken taste is very average."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Nice place to hang out with fam and friends on a laid back weekend.   It has pretty good ambience ,kind staff and amazing food.
Plus point of this place is pool table. Games always add up to our fun n that's what exactly pool table does here."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Quirky and eclectic decor, a welcoming ambience and a great vibe is what you witness upon walking into Hammered. The staff is polite, courteous and quite prompt. The menu has quite a few interesting dishes. The chips and nachos were quite good, a blend of crispy french fries and nachos with different dips, the Kerala beef fry was an absolute melt in the mouth, presented in the form of bite sized morsels with a Kerala parota base, and the chicken wings with their buttermilk glaze was excellent. Each dish was presented with great finesse and the taste set the bar really high. Another visit to sample more of their fusion foods is definitely underway.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Fairly big warehouse like ambiance. Good music and DJ along with plenty of space to even dance.

Ordered around 4 veg starters, not a single one was worth eating it fully. And with the steep prices, this place is NOT worth visiting again.

Avoid.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The place is absolutely wonderful to sit and drink in. Unfortunately, that's the only thing worth doing. Eating is a whole another story. We ordered Nachos, Chicken Wings, Neer Dosa chicken roll and Crispy Lotus.

Nachos was fantastic, but everything else was really bad. In fact the Crispy Lotus was so bad we couldn't eat more than a couple of bites. And the Lotus was boiled! Repeat, Crispy Lotus was boiled! And it was just too sweet. Neer Dosa chicken roll was literally just masala chicken stuff inside Neer dosa. We were expecting something different, but it wasn't. Chicken wings are supposed to be crunchy, this wasn't and it was smothered in over sweet BBQ sauce.

Unfortunately, a restuarant with immense potential is let down by the food. Skip for a better place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  This place is newly opened in HSR. It is located adjacent to the main road that leads to Sarjapur. They got a spacious Ambiance both inside and on terrace. We visited this place for a birthday celebration, and it was awesome. The time we visited, there were some heiniken offer going on. So the process is, they ask you to install a app on your mobile phone, you scan the bar code on your table, and you get 1+1 beer.

Let's start with Food,

1. Tandoori murgh Tikka, it was nice tender Chicken boneless served with One slice of naan and green chutney

2. Onion rings, these were crispy thin slices of onions dip fried, and served with mayo

3. Cheesy potato fries. This was ok ok. Nothing much special about this dish.

Alcohol, we started with Whiskey sour, mister of spices (served with White rum) and bottled beer.

Overall, it's a nice place to hangout. Not much of a crowd. We like this place. Will visit soon.

Ambiance: 4.5/5
Food : 4/5
Service: 4.5/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Tried the veggies pizza , cheesy fries and nachos and the basil tomato mozzarella bruschetta paired with the classic virgin mojito . The pizza was average and couldve been more crispy . The mojito was a perfect delight to have . The fries and nachos lacked a bit of cheese but not a total disappointment. The highlight dish was the dessert - gluten free birds nest . It had blueberry compote with a tinge of orange and orange ice cream with crunchy almonds . The dessert stole the show . The ambience was very hip and this would make a perfect place for a party or dinner .'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Beautiful ambience and innovative food menu they have. Dint like the free cocktail.

They have beautiful spots for pictures and great staff and music.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Hammered is a new place that's opened in HSR. It's right at the junction between Kormangala and Bellandur. Visited this place for a office team lunch and unfortunately the non vegetarian food didn't live up to the mark. My non vegetarian colleagues were highly disappointed. The place is really pretty. Beautiful ambience, great decors and interiors. The place is very cute. The service is very laid back and slow. If you're in a hurry, then please do rethink.
Coming to the Food, tried a whole bunch of starters. The samosas were okay. The Nachos were good, but the Fries soggy. The mushroom money bags were delicious. So so loved this one. It was the star for me. The honey lotus stem was delicious too. Every element in it had lotus, the lotus steam, lotus root and lotus seeds. Delicious!

  What a last night I had in Bangalore !! It was amazing and remembering ! In house shots that are very lit to make someone groove !! Made my last day in Bangalore !!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the new and a nice place to chill out in HSR which has amazing ambience and food. I am happy that we have something like this in HSR where you can drink dance eat as good as SHIFT in hsr.
Staff was also courteous we were serviced by Govind who was quiet dedicated and served us all time carrying smile ?
CouldnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t try much food but was happy to see the beer menu absolutely pocket friendly ?'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  So we happened to visit this place last Friday, looking up for new PUBS in HSR.

Interior is simple and elegant with wide open space. Located right close to the HSR main road. They accept zomato gold, but only on bottled beers, which is a first time experience for me. I mean I have been using gold for almost a year now, but never I came across such policies anywhere. But may be, it differs from restaurant to restaurant.

Well coming to food, we ordered for Murgh ki chaap, it's delicious with a tangy taste and coriander dips.

Overall, it's a nice place for hangout.
Service 3.5/5
Food 4/5"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I really liked this place. Will definitely come here more often. What I really liked about this place is the space. They have a big area with dance floor, dimly lit overlooking ORR. The service was good, the music wasn't too loud, the food was good (I wish they were more experiential with the menu though) coz two things tasted exactly the same. Worth a Visit."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We went here for dinner last weekend. The ambience was nice with some good music. We opted for the rooftop. It was nice and breezy, considering the weather of Bangalore. We ordered nachos, onion rings, crispy corn and chicken drumsticks for starters. The onion rings were a little oily, but others were good. Then we ordered pasta and pizza for main course. It was also good. Overall, a great place to hangout, with an amazing view.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing Lohri night. Food was decent too. Service was polite and ambiance was perfect. We were served by Gopal and Govinda - polite and quick service ?'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Another one in HSR.

Yesterday I visited Indigo XP outlet with my friends, which is opened newly in HSR.

Location: Opposite to Safe House Road, Near by Empire Restaurant.
Parking:They have a small basement and on service road we can park 4 wheeler's.

They have a huge terrace on 5th floor which is operating presently. 4th floor is under construction and opening soon with a dance floor. Overall they have 250+ seating capacity.

Ambiance is quite decent though it gives wow feeling since they have very good view from 5th floor.
Music is the plus point for them. Good music with loud volume and no disturbance.
Restrooms are maintained well. Staffs are trained , friendly and polite.
Food menu quite limited. Ordered for Lamb Chops which was excellent.
Presently they are serving Budweiser and Geist, they don't have KF Draught beer.
Service charge 5% on top.

I appreciate the service of SUCHAN and AMAN, who made our day very special. They were very attentive and helpful. Will be back soon.")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Awesome experience in matters of food.. Being a bong in bangalore, there r cravings for bengali food,but thinking of the price we had to keep postponing it.. Bt now this place has got some delicious bengal delicacies at surprising price(pocket friendly).. Tried moglai paratha, chicken roll, fulka and chicken curry. Also ordered for my family get together. Each dish was worth a compliment... Not much photos are there as were mesmerized by the taste of the dishes that we forgot to click?? one request to start home delivery soon...'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I visited this place for normal team lunch. The foods are awesomely tasty. The taste is of Bengal. Being a Bengali, it's the first restaurant in Bangalore, I found to have the regular Bengal taste in foods. Even though it's indoor seating, the place is small yet it can accommodate 16-20 people at a time.
If u r visiting this place, then mixed veg and chilly fish is a must try. The tawa rooti is same as the Bengal homemade rooti.
If u wanna taste Kolkata 's Mughlai paratha then visit in the evenings.
I am looking forward to place order for home delivery,soon."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened Bengali food joint. I found it suddenly. Initially seeing the humble and simplistic interior we were a bit reluctant to go inside. But though of giving it a try. So ordered moglai paratha and chicken role. Believe me guys, it was the best Kolkata style Moglai paratha I ever have tasted in Bangalore. The chicken kathi role was equally good. We visited a couple of more times and tried different dishes like Chicken bharta, Chicken Butter Masala, Chicken Korma, Chilli Chicken, Fish Manchurian etc. I must say that all of these items were extremely tasty and the price was very reasonable. A must try for everyone who are looking for great tasty Bengali food without worrying about the price. And not looking for swanky places.')]

  The place is absolutely wonderful to sit and drink in. Unfortunately, that's the only thing worth doing. Eating is a whole another story. We ordered Nachos, Chicken Wings, Neer Dosa chicken roll and Crispy Lotus.

Nachos was fantastic, but everything else was really bad. In fact the Crispy Lotus was so bad we couldn't eat more than a couple of bites. And the Lotus was boiled! Repeat, Crispy Lotus was boiled! And it was just too sweet. Neer Dosa chicken roll was literally just masala chicken stuff inside Neer dosa. We were expecting something different, but it wasn't. Chicken wings are supposed to be crunchy, this wasn't and it was smothered in over sweet BBQ sauce.

Unfortunately, a restuarant with immense potential is let down by the food. Skip for a better place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  This place is newly opened in HSR. It is located adjacent to the main road that leads to Sarjapur. They got a spacious Ambiance both inside and on terrace. We visited this place for a birthday celebration, and it was awesome. The time we visited, there were some heiniken offer going on. So the process is, they ask you to install a app on your mobile phone, you scan the bar code on your table, and you get 1+1 beer.

Let's start with Food,

1. Tandoori murgh Tikka, it was nice tender Chicken boneless served with One slice of naan and green chutney

2. Onion rings, these were crispy thin slices of onions dip fried, and served with mayo

3. Cheesy potato fries. This was ok ok. Nothing much special about this dish.

Alcohol, we started with Whiskey sour, mister of spices (served with White rum) and bottled beer.

Overall, it's a nice place to hangout. Not much of a crowd. We like this place. Will visit soon.

Ambiance: 4.5/5
Food : 4/5
Service: 4.5/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Tried the veggies pizza , cheesy fries and nachos and the basil tomato mozzarella bruschetta paired with the classic virgin mojito . The pizza was average and couldve been more crispy . The mojito was a perfect delight to have . The fries and nachos lacked a bit of cheese but not a total disappointment. The highlight dish was the dessert - gluten free birds nest .   Hammered is a new place that's opened in HSR. It's right at the junction between Kormangala and Bellandur. Visited this place for a office team lunch and unfortunately the non vegetarian food didn't live up to the mark. My non vegetarian colleagues were highly disappointed. The place is really pretty. Beautiful ambience, great decors and interiors. The place is very cute. The service is very laid back and slow. If you're in a hurry, then please do rethink.
Coming to the Food, tried a whole bunch of starters. The samosas were okay. The Nachos were good, but the Fries soggy. The mushroom money bags were delicious. So so loved this one. It was the star for me. The honey lotus stem was delicious too. Every element in it had lotus, the lotus steam, lotus root and lotus seeds. Delicious!

reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place on sunday evening..
*Ambience is nice , big and spacious.
*Coming to food , we ordered many dishes loaded french fries , chicken tikka , chicken golgappa and sliders burgers. Food was good.
*Drinks - we ordered LlIT and beer , very few beers were available , thats was disappointing. LIIT was good.
*MUSIC was average , they need to work on their music.
* Staff were polite and helpful.
Overall 3.5 star'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It's newly opened in hsr layout. The place is huge . Indoor seating is basically in a huge hall nicely transformed into a place for dining. A huge balcony for outdoor seating. However , we ordered a hukkah just to find out they ran out of coal at 6 in evening. Also had bad experiences with the billing as we had few discount vouchers and there policies were little twisted with that.Our experience in other outlets have been better I'd say."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  We had called to ask about the availabilty of draught beer. They said its available and we reached the place now they say they dont have it.
So the visit is spoilt.. kudos 'Hammered' for the great experience.
The fries and nachos are not homemade so nothing special about it, chilli chicken taste is very average."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Coolest pubs in HSR, ambiance, food and service all are worthy enough for the place to earn four stars. For vegetarians I recommend pannee pav bhaji for sure. Must visit.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Hammered finally is in hsr layout... the ambience was great ... Nice place to chill out with a gang. Loved it

We had ordered bruschetta, nachos which was very tasty and pizza could have been better in taste
Mocktails(summer mocktail and excotic) was suggested by Jitu(waiter) that was really superb. Thanks to him'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Hammered hsr ultimate place. Its starting from sarjapur road. Nice ambience and nice place for hangout. Big place and right place to do a party.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Fairly new place for HSR . Interesting high open ambience . Attentive courteous staff. Good food . Yuri thanks for taking care of us . Will go back again'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice place to hang out with fam and friends on a laid back weekend. No dance floor is a disappointment as the place plays amazing music ( you need to stay post 10, that when the music actually pumps up). Have 2 distinct sitting areas, ground floor for non-smokers and first floor for smokers ( with a view of the Agara lake). They have a nice pool table, in case you wanna have a friendly challenge over a tower of beer. Food was good and I would rate 4/5. Over the place is a 4 out of 5. A must visit for peeps staying in and around HSR.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Visited last night. We ordered food as soon we settled down. It took them an hour to get some basic starters. The bruschetta was cold and the bread was too hard to eat. Fries were okay but slow service spoiled the fun.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It has pretty good ambience ,kind staff and amazing food.
Plus point of this place is pool table. Games always add up to our fun n that's what exactly pool table does here."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Quirky and eclectic decor, a welcoming ambience and a great vibe is what you witness upon walking into Hammered. The staff is polite, courteous and quite prompt. The menu has quite a few interesting dishes. The chips and nachos were quite good, a blend of crispy french fries and nachos with different dips, the Kerala beef fry was an absolute melt in the mouth, presented in the form of bite sized morsels with a Kerala parota base, and the chicken wings with their buttermilk glaze was excellent. Each dish was presented with great finesse and the taste set the bar really high. Another visit to sample more of their fusion foods is definitely underway.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  My rating is for decor ,ambiance of the outlet it feels like you are sitting in lawn or an open area

  Fairly big warehouse like ambiance. Good music and DJ along with plenty of space to even dance.
Drinks were good, however it was the food which was a huge disappointment.

Ordered around 4 veg starters, not a single one was worth eating it fully. And with the steep prices, this place is NOT worth visiting again.

Avoid.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The place is absolutely wonderful to sit and drink in. Unfortunately, that's the only thing worth doing. Eating is a whole another story. We ordered Nachos, Chicken Wings, Neer Dosa chicken roll and Crispy Lotus.

Nachos was fantastic, but everything else was really bad. In fact the Crispy Lotus was so bad we couldn't eat more than a couple of bites. And the Lotus was boiled! Repeat, Crispy Lotus was boiled! And it was just too sweet. Neer Dosa chicken roll was literally just masala chicken stuff inside Neer dosa. We were expecting something different, but it wasn't. Chicken wings are supposed to be crunchy, this wasn't and it was smothered in over sweet BBQ sauce.

Unfortunately, a restuarant with immense potential is let down by the food. Skip for a better place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This beautifully designed place is a perfect venue for a wonderful evening. The decor, the arrangement, the menu, the services... everything was just perfect. Loved the place.???'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This place is newly opened in HSR. It is located adjacent to the main road that leads to Sarjapur. They got a spacious Ambiance both inside and on terrace. We visited this place for a birthday celebration, and it was awesome. The time we visited, there were some heiniken offer going on. So the process is, they ask you to install a app on your mobile phone, you scan the bar code on your table, and you get 1+1 beer.

Let's start with Food,

1. Tandoori murgh Tikka, it was nice tender Chicken boneless served with One slice of naan and green chutney

2. Onion rings, these were crispy thin slices of onions dip fried, and served with mayo

3. Cheesy potato fries. This was ok ok. Nothing much special about this dish.

Alcohol, we started with Whiskey sour, mister of spices (served with White rum) and bottled beer.

Overall, it's a nice place to hangout. Not much of a crowd. We like this place. Will visit soon.

Ambiance: 4.5/5
Food : 4/5
Service: 4.5/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Tried the veggies pizza , cheesy fries and nachos and the basil tomato mozzarella bruschetta paired with the classic virgin mojito . The pizza was average and couldve been more crispy . The mojito was a perfect delight to have . The fries and nachos lacked a bit of cheese but not a total disappointment. The highlight dish was the dessert - gluten free birds nest . It had blueberry compote with a tinge of orange and orange ice cream with crunchy almonds . The dessert stole the show . The ambience was very hip and this would make a perfect place for a party or dinner .'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Beautiful ambience and innovative food menu they have. Dint like the free cocktail.

However we ordered BhelPuri Prawns which was okayish! , neither chatpata nor spicy.

And Lebanease Sambousek Lamb which was less in quantity but amazing at taste. And then beer normal.

They have beautiful spots for pictures and great staff and music.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Hammered is a new place that's opened in HSR. It's right at the junction between Kormangala and Bellandur. Visited this place for a office team lunch and unfortunately the non vegetarian food didn't live up to the mark. My non vegetarian colleagues were highly disappointed. The place is really pretty. Beautiful ambience, great decors and interiors. The place is very cute. The service is very laid back and slow. If you're in a hurry, then please do rethink.
Coming to the Food, tried a whole bunch of starters. The samosas were okay. The Nachos were good, but the Fries soggy. The mushroom money bags were delicious. So so loved this one. It was the star for me. The honey lotus stem was delicious too. Every element in it had lotus, the lotus steam, lotus root and lotus seeds. Delicious!
Ravioli, veg pizza were decent. The desserts were really good. But highly expensive. Tried the filter Kaapi ice cream, pavlova, tiramusu, and souffle and Brownie. The chocolate and berry was okay."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED

  This newly opened place in hsr is going to be lit in no time.

Gramd opening , amazing offers.

I wasn't expecting initially that the staff would be good, polite, courteous since its new and might take time to adjust.

But the service has been great. I visited the place 3 times already.

Raaj is one amongst the staff and he did a great job .
He has always been welcoming and served ua throughout.

With this pace, this place will soon become one of the most happening place , located at Agra lake junction.

We ordered kerala style chicken starter , chicken lolipop, loaded cheesy fries & nachos ( liked the most )

Orderd veg pizza ( under average , didn't like the quantity and the taste )

Apart from it, the place is so huge and happening.

Must visit :)"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

name: House Of Seitan
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place caught our attention on a Sunday afternoon while shopping on the busy Indiranagar 100 ft toad. Went for a quick bite and tried the Seitan sourdough bread sandwich and a banana shake. In itself the sandwich was good. Seitan the meat substitute was tasty in the sandwich. But I wish there was more quantity or some side. For the price we pay, I felt it wasnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t much...'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I'll let you know at the outset that their options are limited, but all taste good and are filling. They have sandwiches (burgers and pita as well), salads and beverages. The standard ingredient is Seitan, which is pretty much gluten and soya that's been processed to resemble mock meat. The place ideal for vegetarians, vegans and those looking to transition.
Don't expect anything too fancy in their ingredients as everything (except the breads and vegetables obviously) are made in house. I had a sandwich with caramelised onion vinaigrette and pesto as well as a carrot and ginger juice. It came with a small portion of salad (plus points for using local raw mangoes).
The sandwich, though tasty was falling apart either due to the bread thickness or amount of filling. Will probably go back to try a burger or pita."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  SEITAN - Finally in India.
This is the only place in India that serves SEITAN.

For us Vegetarians this is paradise, SEITAN is super high in protein(45gms) and I was pretty amazed at the variety of SEITAN they serve in the form of Healthy Burgers, Pita, Sandwiches, salads and more.

The team and the founders were very patient to explain and educate people about SEITAN.

Lip smacking yet nutritious and super healthy!

Give your taste buds a Seitan spin!!')]

[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Fabulous place for great pizzas. They are quite large , thin crust base with delish toppings. The ambiance is casual with excellent service.

The kids love garlic bread. So we ordered a portion. Eat them while they are still hot and the cheese just oozes. We ordered the beach- which is a seafood pizza which has all the seafood topped with a Bachammal cheese top. For the meat lovers I recommend the wolf wolf - which is a lamb mince and que pasa pizza which has the chorizo topping. The wolf wolf scored for us over the que pasa pizza. The pizzas are more than 12 inches so itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s filling for two. great place to hang out with family.

  Brikoven - A great pizza place ?
this is their second outlet in the city, situated on the 80ft road, Indiranagar. 

The place has very great ambience, and very spacious compared to church street outlet. The feel, the music played, the vibes here are just awesome! ?

We ordered, 
Quattro formaggi pizza, the pizza was of four cheese and the taste was very good and amazing ?, it's a must try on the menu! 
Diavola is tasty and great pizza to try on the menu! 
Also try the smokey marzano pizza here! 
Loevd the taste of the Pizzas here, Love to visit Brikoven again and again for their great service and great taste! 

? Best pizzas in town! 
? Love the ambience here! ?
? Best interiors and spacious pizzeria!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Rating 4/5

Brik opened in Indiranagar a few weeks ago, and we finally got a chance to head there. Much larger than the church street outlet, the decor was also much better IMO.

Service was superb, my daughter commented that things like napkins got replaced as soon as she used her current one!

The pizzas - as good as always. The only disappointment was the "#16. Bird in hand" pizza, I'd not order that again. The mushroom pizza with the truffle oil was awesome, so much of flavor bursting with each bite. The pepperoni is a classic, and was perfect.

Another thing I liked was the diet coke was at Rs. 60 only, not a very marked up price.

Definitely very happy to have Brik open up so close to home, and right next to Milano Ice creams! Perfect combo for sure...

CoE : paid for the meal, this is a new outlet and my first time, been to the other outlet multiple times.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Craving for the best pizza in Bangalore?
Brik Oven is your answer
I am extremely pleased that they have finally opened in Indiranagar and a bigger place. 
I always have eaten the Margarita but this time we ordered the White Fungi too and it was amazing! 
Please do keep up the good work and will definitely come back soon for more.

  Royanna definitely has potential to serve good food, will assume they are having teething problems as they are new. first time I had their chicken palao it was outstanding, grains flaking away the hint of ghee in the background and spices, although the 2nd time I had it the spice level had been mellowed down a lot. it needs to go back up again.
the chops were military on par, great gravy with it, the kebab was outstanding, the chicken fry needs some work and so does the chilli chicken, chilli chicken needs a lot more than chilli as that was the only profile coming through.

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is a new restaurant that opened a couple of buildings right next to our office.
Decided to try it out.
The first thing that stands out is the ambience. They've got a unique look of an actual power station going and all the waiters are dressed up to reflect the same.

The Service was pretty prompt and we were treated well.

Food turned out great. Since I'm a veggie. I went in for the mushroom twisters and a sphaghetti aglio olio.

Was pleased to say they tasted great.

We got a kiwi mocktail and a couple of desserts on the house. The cheesecake and the choco lava cake were top notch.

Looking forward to more visits and trying their pizza out when they start making it.")]

[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Located opposite to ESI quarters beside Pulla Reddy sweet shop in Indiranagar. Small shop with very less sitting option.
They are mostly into Bengali cuisine and that made me enter the place. I went in to have chicken roll but ended up ordering Mughlai paratha with egg and chicken and got it parcelled. I felt the items were bit expensive.
I thought it would be egg and chicken stuffed paratha but it was egg stuffed along with chicken gravy.
Coming to the taste, the chicken gravy was yummy but the mughlai paratha was a let down. The layer of maida was too thick and not cooked authenticity was missing. I hope they improve over the time and give us a chance to relish some food again.')]

  Opened in March last year this joint is a small version of Mary Cafe that's on the Thippasandra main road near the Durga Temple. I'm a regular to this place and have been eating their food since the day they opened up the shop. Inside, the place is setup neatly with few tables and they have done a good job with the interiors.

All in all, a nice place with good enough food with little pinch to pocket.")]

name: House Of Seitan
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place caught our attention on a Sunday afternoon while shopping on the busy Indiranagar 100 ft toad. Went for a quick bite and tried the Seitan sourdough bread sandwich and a banana shake. In itself the sandwich was good. Seitan the meat substitute was tasty in the sandwich. But I wish there was more quantity or some side. For the price we pay, I felt it wasnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t much...'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I'll let you know at the outset that their options are limited, but all taste good and are filling. They have sandwiches (burgers and pita as well), salads and beverages. The standard ingredient is Seitan, which is pretty much gluten and soya that's been processed to resemble mock meat. The place ideal for vegetarians, vegans and those looking to transition.
Don't expect anything too fancy in their ingredients as everything (except the breads and vegetables obviously) are made in house. I had a sandwich with caramelised onion vinaigrette and pesto as well as a carrot and ginger juice. It came with a small portion of salad (plus points for using local raw mangoes).
The sandwich, though tasty was falling apart either due to the bread thickness or amount of filling. Will probably go back to try a burger or pita."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  SEITAN - Finally in India.
This is the only place in India that serves SEITAN.

For us Vegetarians this is paradise, SEITAN is super high in protein(45gms) and I was pretty amazed at the variety of SEITAN they serve in the form of Healthy Burgers, Pita, Sandwiches, salads and more.

The team and the founders were very patient to explain and educate people about SEITAN.

Lip smacking yet nutritious and super healthy!

Give your taste buds a Seitan spin!!')]

1. Tofu Katsu Curry - Flavourful curry with fried tofu served with sticky rice. Highly recommend this.

2. Veg Skewers - Flavours were on point but a bit too salty perhaps. Would be better if they can tone down the salt.

3. Shitake & Spinach Gimbap - was great, really liked it.

Uber chic Asian decor. But itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s a skinny alley converted into a restaurant where even average sized people would feel large. address: 872/A, Ground Floor, 80 Feet Road, HAL 2nd Stage, Indiranagar, Bangalore
name: Brik Oven
dish_liked: Garlic Bread, Big Bang Shake, Smokey Marzano Pizza
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Fabulous place for great pizzas. They are quite large , thin crust base with delish toppings. The ambiance is casual with excellent service.

The kids love garlic bread. So we ordered a portion. Eat them while they are still hot and the cheese just oozes. We ordered the beach- which is a seafood pizza which has all the seafood topped with a Bachammal cheese top. For the meat lovers I recommend the wolf wolf - which is a lamb mince and que pasa pizza which has the chorizo topping. The wolf wolf scored for us over the que pasa pizza. The pizzas are more than 12 inches so itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s filling for two. great place to hang out with family.

alifeofjoysite.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Brikoven - A great pizza place ?
this is their second outlet in the city, situated on the 80ft road, Indiranagar. 

The place has very great ambience, and very spacious compared to church street outlet. The feel, the music played, the vibes here are just awesome! ?

We ordered, 
Quattro formaggi pizza, the pizza was of four cheese and the taste was very good and amazing ?, it's a must try on the menu! 
Diavola is tasty and great pizza to try on the menu! 
Also try the smokey marzano pizza here! 
Loevd the taste of the Pizzas here, Love to visit Brikoven again and again for their great service and great taste! 

? Best pizzas in town! 
? Love the ambience here! ?
? Best interiors and spacious pizzeria!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Rating 4/5

Brik opened in Indiranagar a few weeks ago, and we finally got a chance to head there. Much larger than the church street outlet, the decor was also much better IMO.

Service was superb, my daughter commented that things like napkins got replaced as soon as she used her current one!

The pizzas - as good as always. The only disappointment was the "#16. Bird in hand" pizza, I'd not order that again. The mushroom pizza with the truffle oil was awesome, so much of flavor bursting with each bite. The pepperoni is a classic, and was perfect.

Another thing I liked was the diet coke was at Rs. 60 only, not a very marked up price.

Definitely very happy to have Brik open up so close to home, and right next to Milano Ice creams! Perfect combo for sure...

CoE : paid for the meal, this is a new outlet and my first time, been to the other outlet multiple times.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Craving for the best pizza in Bangalore?
Brik Oven is your answer
I am extremely pleased that they have finally opened in Indiranagar and a bigger place. 
I always have eaten the Margarita but this time we ordered the White Fungi too and it was amazing! 
Please do keep up the good work and will definitely come back soon for more. 
Also their shakes, garlic bread with cheese and my husband's favorite - blue cheese dip are just mouth watering and you just can't stop :)

reshamthevegetarianfoodie.wordpress.com"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Beautiful ambience, authentic Italian pizzas (Margherita and the Anna) with the best cheesy garlic bread and minty dip. Courteous staff and speedy service. Definitely going back to try their freak shakes and the rest of the pizzas!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Dont think theres much that can go wrong when u dine here. The experience was good like always. Really loved their casual, informam ambience with some good instrumental music. The food and drinks were a delight! Thoroughly enjoyed the pizza....'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Best place in Bangalore! So glad we have another branch. BO will always be my top choice of restaurants whenever I have to go out. Do try out the bird in hand and nutty professor.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A weekend spent eating good food is a weekend well spent! Brik Oven was fabulous. We ordered two pizzas The Anna and Red Cotta, and both were perfect. Even my 3 year old daughter enjoyed the two slices without any fuss! The pizza was very soft and after a long time I had such good thin crust pizzas! The Big Bang shake was also good! We loved the ambience, a very chic and minimalist. I enjoyed the open kitchen where I was able to see my pizza going in the brick oven! Congratulations and best of luck Team Brik Oven!')]

address: 788, JK Plaza, 12th Main, 2nd Stage, Indiranagar, Bangalore
name: House Of Seitan
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place caught our attention on a Sunday afternoon while shopping on the busy Indiranagar 100 ft toad. Went for a quick bite and tried the Seitan sourdough bread sandwich and a banana shake. In itself the sandwich was good. Seitan the meat substitute was tasty in the sandwich. But I wish there was more quantity or some side. For the price we pay, I felt it wasnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t much...'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I'll let you know at the outset that their options are limited, but all taste good and are filling. They have sandwiches (burgers and pita as well), salads and beverages. The standard ingredient is Seitan, which is pretty much gluten and soya that's been processed to resemble mock meat. The place ideal for vegetarians, vegans and those looking to transition.
Don't expect anything too fancy in their ingredients as everything (except the breads and vegetables obviously) are made in house. I had a sandwich with caramelised onion vinaigrette and pesto as well as a carrot and ginger juice. It came with a small portion of salad (plus points for using local raw mangoes).
The sandwich, though tasty was falling apart either due to the bread thickness or amount of filling. Will probably go back to try a burger or pita."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  SEITAN - Finally in India.
This is the only place in India that serves SEITAN.

For us Vegetarians this is paradise, SEITAN is super high in protein(45gms) and I was pretty amazed at the variety of SEITAN they serve in the form of Healthy Burgers, Pita, Sandwiches, salads and more.

The team and the founders were very patient to explain and educate people about SEITAN.

Lip smacking yet nutritious and super healthy!

Give your taste buds a Seitan spin!!')]

name: Power House Pitstsa
cuisines: Continental, Burger, Desserts, Sandwich, Italian, Pizza, Bakery, Salad
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is a new restaurant that opened a couple of buildings right next to our office.
Decided to try it out.
The first thing that stands out is the ambience. They've got a unique look of an actual power station going and all the waiters are dressed up to reflect the same.

The Service was pretty prompt and we were treated well.

Food turned out great. Since I'm a veggie. I went in for the mushroom twisters and a sphaghetti aglio olio.

Was pleased to say they tasted great.

We got a kiwi mocktail and a couple of desserts on the house. The cheesecake and the choco lava cake were top notch.

Looking forward to more visits and trying their pizza out when they start making it.")]

[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Being a vegetarian foodie, I have tried most of the vegetarian friendly places in bangalore and this is a good addition to it.

This is a brand new restaurant which offers mostly Noth Indian food with fancy names.

Below are few items I tried:

1. House special Pani puri: Always loved Pani puri but the taste here was just average. A suggestion to give meetha with the paani.

2. Charcoal grilled babycorn: They were perfect with the right balance of crispyness and softness. Loved the mint chutney which came with the dish as well.

3. Spicy Indian: A Guava Chilli mocktail which was lip smacking and refreshing.

4. Paneer makhani with butter naan: I could have this over and over again... It was that good! The Paneer was cooked well and the gravy wasn't very sweet which was very delicious.

Overall, this restaurant has good vegetarian food and service is also fast. Costed 1k for 3 people with the Zomato gold option of 1+1 on food. Will definitely visit again to try more dishes here."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

  I had been here with a few friends to try out this new place a few days ago, and one of their owners informed us that it is a new place that has opened about 15 days ago. However, was extremely disappointed. This place is trying very hard to be different, but will fail miserably in the long run. The food was okayish in taste, and overpriced for the small quantity they are serving. 

For example, I have been to plenty of places where for the same price of an appetizer, I can get a quantity good enough for 2-3 people. 

Further, most of their appetizers we had are such that it can be made at home, better than what they make.

Soups were meh, and lacking in flavor. Again, quantity for the price we are paying here is a big issue.

Will not visit again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Had been to this place last week on a week day so it was not very crowded we could get the table easily. Another reason to go here was for Gold offer.
There was an other restaurant here which is now Fusion Theory, they have retained the same ambience. Service was good and staff were friendly.
Coming to food we ordered papad nachos which was very different and unique, their special pani puri which had 3 tastes infused into it, was more sweetish, I like spicy so didn't enjoy it much. One more mushroom starter which wevordered also very nice.

[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The quantity is more than enough, but the price does not quantify the quality. The rice was undercooked, so flavourless. Need to improve the taste and quality for sure'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have admitted my mom in a reputed hospital in Jayanagar where outside food is strictly not allowed and their canteen closes by 9:30 PM. My home is in Whitefield. Almost after 1:30 hrs journey I reached the hospital by 10:00 PM. I was super hungry. Around 10:30 only I started searching for food in Zomato, I donÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t want to eat heavy but want something hot and steamed. What would be a better choice than momos? So, found this Momo Blues! Ordered both momo blues oz and shrimp momos - I was totally surprised by the quality and taste of the momos. The momos were really steaming hot and soft. Even in many big restaurants, the momos I had were hard and dry! These momos tasted fresh and juicy... if you are staying in and around of Koramangala and if you are a momo lover, then your go-to place is momo blues! Their shrimp momos worth the every penny! They were perfect as well!
Thanks to ZomatoÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s delivery guy! He came real quick and saved me from my hunger!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  Having been a huge fan of the chainÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s first (?) outlet in Saket, I was chomping at the bit to try itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s outlet in my city.   I like this place quite a lot. Indoor and outdoor seating options with an amazing ambience is going to pull you to this place quite often. I had a iced mocha and an avocado sandwich.   Really like the ambience here. Coffee is obviously superb, and the food is not bad and decently priced. They have a nice selection of lunch/cafe items.   A good day begins with good breakfast . I thought of trying out this place for breakfast on Saturday morning.
This is a very beautiful home turned into cafe . Lovely place with pleasant ambiance both indoor and outdoor seating .

We ordered for Free ranged poached eggs on chefs recommendation , honestly we were disappointed with this since the bread was burnt .
I ordered for falafel flat bread . This was the best and I feel it is a must try . It is falafel with pita bread n pumpkin hummus . Was totally in love with the taste .
In addition we tried their baked sweet potato fries and it was super yummy . Just tried their cold brew coffee .
Since this place is known for coffee I would love to try new things during my next visit .

Overall it was a good experience and the staff here are really concerned with customer satisfaction which I personally appreciate.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu opened its doors in Blore after a successful run in Hyderabad. We went here for dinner & on recommendation by the manager ordered Korameenu Vepudu, Konaseema Mamsam Vepudu & Kodi Raju gari polao & Apricot delight(best of the lot) in desserts I loved the food..no complaints. But the service is bit confusing. They need to brush up their skills of serving in a restaurant at peak hours specially. I did not quite like the ambiance also reminded of Durga Puja Theme pandals back home. Pricing is a bit high compared to quantity served. Will visit again to try their unique variety of biryani & polao'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had been yesterday to this amazing place with friends over lunch.. They had the food served in banana leaf for the 1st time since it opened. We ordered Konaseema Kodi Vepudu and Bamboo Chicken as non veg starters and Mokkajoanna Vepudu (Baby Corn dish) as veg starter.. The bamboo chicken was spicy to the likes of everyone. Distinct bamboo flavour takes the dish to different level.. For mains, we took Ulavacharu Kodi pulao, Dal fry, rotis and Veg salad.. They were very good..

I would highly recommend this place to all if they want to try Authentic Andhra food..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Last week visited Ulavacharu with my friends. Food taste and quality were pretty decent except desserts.

Ambience is quite different and good.

Ratings:

  A typical Andhra reasturant like all the other reasturant, the ambience is not that great , it's got a raw feel, but doens't seem exciting , the food was like any other Andhra reasturant , nothing different. The customer service is pretty average, pricing is way too high.. it's like any other Andhra reasturant.."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I need to explore this place more. My first experience was not so great. We ordered Raju kodi biryani. Rice was sticky, there were rice lumps and pieces were hard and bland.
Got it replaced with Mutton biryani and it was just normal biryani.
I would say its on the pricy side atleast by 50 bucks.
Ambience is rustic and reminds of rural set up and Granny's house.
I somehow feel they are really good at what they are preparing, i just need to explore more or go at the right time."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  What a brilliant place \U0001f929 let's get straight to the food. I had Telangana mamsam Kura and kulcha. It was like a marriage made in heaven. The mutton was brilliantly cooked, the gravy was so flavourful. I cannot stop gushing about how brilliant it was. A little bit too oily, no doubt. But it hit all the right notes!

I also tried the uluvacharu Kodi pulao.. the biriyani was definitely good but nothing extraordinary. Definitely going back there for more!

A small feedback would be to also explain the various dishes that you have since the entire menu has the Telugu names. It would be easier for the customers to understand what they're ordering."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It was my first time visit to the place and trust me I was awestruck with the entrance and then with the interior but the food was as tasty as the entrance and the stuff being so polite and asking for your comfort zone and making you explain the food items as the menu for the north indian to understand is difficult. The way the atmosphere they have maintained is beautiful and the Manager. Suresh was excellent at the service he suggested us the best spicy biryani - Gadwal Kodi Pulao and we ordered it and damn yummmmmy!! Infact I took one parcel to send to my city surat,gujarat with a friend next day and it still dint get spoilt. However we ordered three parcel but they were out of stock :( so had to send just one. But beautiful experience and not too pricy. Thank you for everything!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Koramangala has new destination for another Authentic cusine and its Ualavacharu. Its opened in the prime location and easy to find. Their Ambience is mind blowing. Starting from the entrance to every corner the decoration is very well pictured. They are 2 branches in Hyderabad and this is their 1st branch in Bangalore.

Coming to food, I loved Raju gari kodi pulav- which was little gravish, spicy and is different from any other biryanis.

For starters we ordered Kona seema kodi vepudu- which is semi gravy and fiery. Chapala Vepudu was crispy and good.

Main course we took Roti along Andhra Kodi curry which was spicy and had fine taste. Gadwal Kodi pulao was good in taste. Apricot Delight desert is a must try.

All the food are spicy and this would an irresistible place for Andhra cuisine lovers. Will definitely mark this place for Andhra meal next time. Worth trying. !'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Another badly wanted to go restaurant with lot of expectations. It was a Saturday evening and this was a new place in town. The interiors of this place is very good and we were pretty impressed with the variety of pulao/biryani options we could see on the menu.

We did ordered almost three different pulao and starters. The Andra style starters were good to start with and than comes the biryani. The presentation of the biryani was good but the biryaniÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s were not up-to the badge. What started with good experience ended with a satisfactory note.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu is the new Andhra speciality restaurant which has recently opened up in Kormangala,Bangalore.
The decor is done beautifully with Lord Krishna idol,stone pillars,wooden waterfall structure and a whole lot of comfortable seatings.
Being a south Indian I absolutely love Andhra flavours which is spicy and laced with richness of ghee.just the way I like it ?
I personally loved the Ulvacharu,Bangla Kodi,Konaseema Kodi Vepudu,Raju Gari Kodi Pulav.
Do visit this legendary place which is famous in Hyderabad and now serving delicacies in Bengaluru?

thegalwhoblogs.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ulavacharu the restuarant which brings the finest delicacies of andhra prsdesh to our own Koramangala.

Ulavacharu itself a dish prepared from horse grame which is very famous in Andhra Pradesh.

Rustic Ambience which gives you the feel of old homes in village.

Welcoming Indian desserts were
Khaja and badusha.

Bangla Kodi a uniquely prepared dish where boneless chicken stuffed in a potato pockets.

The food was amazing especially Raju Gari kodi pulao.

And Kona Seema Kodi vepudu this was the spiciest chicken Starter I had here.

The gutti vankaya pulao this was amazing.

Tandoori fish don't miss out this guy's it's a must have here.A full size koramenu cooked with right amount of masala.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu has arrived in bangalore! Located next to empire koramangala, near to jnc College. This road is like Food capital for bangalore. Ulavacharu is right on location. I had heard of this restaurant which has some unique dishes in its menu. Ambience is quite good with soothing decors. I ordered their signature dish rajugari kodi palav, Bangla kodi. They gave rava laddu as complimentary which tasted excellent. Bangla kodi was crispy, but few pieces of chicken were chewy which they can work on. I am sure they will. Raju Gari kodi palav is one of its kind, it was flavourful, kind of semi gravy, tasted really good. Palav was really hot when they served had to wait for some time before I got started, chicken pieces were tender and juicy. The raitha went well with the palav. Service is efficient. Overall ulavacharu is here to make a mark.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ulavacharu's inception is an effort towards attending a void that was prevalent in every metropolitan decorated with multi cuisines and themed restaurants. Our team from Wanna Know Where We Eat? stepped in to experience the bliss, taste, tradition and flavour of Ulavacharu today and are still in the hangover of the taste and tradition that they offered us. We rate this place 4.8/5.0 after evaluating all the 25 factors that we consider before rating a restaurant. The experience we had over there was next to perfection and the food served over there was a pure bliss."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

address: 1304, Ground Floor, 9th Cross, 20th Main, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Baba Chatkora
dish_liked: Dal Makhani, Thali, Matka Lassi
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  As always my goto order chaap. New outlet in Jp nagar will give you a feel of north India with its beautiful ambiance and punjabi songs playing around. Super crowded in weekends. Should go early to block your seats.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened restaurant which deals with your craving for dal makhni. A dhaba but in an uptown style. The service is a bit slow, but the food and the kebabs are yummm. Also, the green chutney is worth licking your fingers. Nice place for a fam jam!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Newly opened in JP Nagar, this place is close to RV Dental college. We went on a lazy afternoon to check out this place. The ambience of this place is very nice, with decent staff ready to offer good service. Coming to food, the menu is simple yet good. From their lassi to their thali, everything is authentic Punjabi style.
Overall, would recommend you to try this place once. A good place to have decent food.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Baba Chatkora is one of the options in JP Nagar for rejoicing authentic North Indian delicacies.

Visited this place only on the second day of after they opened. The place is nicely done. Bollywood and Punjabi numbers played at the backdrop gives a nice vibe to the place.

The food was decent.
We ordered Matka Lassi, Dhabha style Paneer, Ghobi matar and Butter naan.
Expected more from the Dhabha style paneer but it was the same as you would get in any any other North Indian restaurant.
The Matka Lassi was really thick and tasted great but the portion was pretty small.

A decent option for family dining but a bit overpriced. When you have so many options nearby and when a customer is looking for places which offers great value for money or something exemplary, Baba Chatkora fails miserably on that regard.

Happy eating!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Yay! Baba Chatkora is in JP Nagar now. Everything about this place is splendid. The food, the ambiance, the friendly staff and of course the music.

We ordered:
Soya Chaaps
Kulcha
And paneer starters
Plus they have the winter special menu too, and the gajar ka halwa is en pointe!

If you are craving for North Indian delicacies, look no further.')]

address: 10, Opposite Forum Mall, Taverekere, Suddagunte Palya, BTM, Bangalore
name: Fogg
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.
Greek salad - Lettuce, Olives and Feta Cheese in the perfect mix.
Vergin Fried chicken - Chicken Fried with a coated batter. Tasted good.
Mix sause pasta - Penne Rigate Pasta with chicken cubes in a mixed sauce.
3 cheese pesto pizza - Generous servings of Cheddar, Parmesan and Mozarella Cheese layered on the Thin crust Pizza base tasted really well. You could feel the Cheese in every bite.
Chicken wrap - Chicken Cubes with veggies wrapped in Arabian Bread.
Chicken Nachos - Julienned chicken pieces and cheesw spread on Crisp Nachos.
Chicken pot rice - Jasmine rice with a mild Green Curry Gravy with veggies. Very flavourful and tasty.
Prawns kudla de Fogg - A preparation similar to the Prawns Ghee Roast with a similar texture and taste.
Excellent service and good food. Had a pleasant experience.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  Late night sometimes idli, dosa surfuce my hunger. Recently found a new place , basically a old tiny place serving idli, dosa.   Being a vegetarian foodie, I have tried most of the vegetarian friendly places in bangalore and this is a good addition to it.

This is a brand new restaurant which offers mostly Noth Indian food with fancy names.

Below are few items I tried:

1. House special Pani puri: Always loved Pani puri but the taste here was just average. A suggestion to give meetha with the paani.

2. Charcoal grilled babycorn: They were perfect with the right balance of crispyness and softness. Loved the mint chutney which came with the dish as well.

3. Spicy Indian: A Guava Chilli mocktail which was lip smacking and refreshing.

4. Paneer makhani with butter naan: I could have this over and over again... It was that good! The Paneer was cooked well and the gravy wasn't very sweet which was very delicious.

Overall, this restaurant has good vegetarian food and service is also fast. Costed 1k for 3 people with the Zomato gold option of 1+1 on food. Will definitely visit again to try more dishes here."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

  I had been here with a few friends to try out this new place a few days ago, and one of their owners informed us that it is a new place that has opened about 15 days ago. However, was extremely disappointed. This place is trying very hard to be different, but will fail miserably in the long run. The food was okayish in taste, and overpriced for the small quantity they are serving. 

For example, I have been to plenty of places where for the same price of an appetizer, I can get a quantity good enough for 2-3 people. 

Further, most of their appetizers we had are such that it can be made at home, better than what they make.

Soups were meh, and lacking in flavor. Again, quantity for the price we are paying here is a big issue.

address: 15, Bannerghatta Main Road, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Le Arabia
dish_liked: Chicken Biryani
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The quantity is more than enough, but the price does not quantify the quality. The rice was undercooked, so flavourless. Need to improve the taste and quality for sure'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

reviews_list:

  Best Kerala restaurant in the vicinity.Nice spacious interiors and good service.

Apart from the above they give payasam,upperi,rasam,pappadam,one veg side dish(got bhindi masala which was very good) and a good amount of rice...all for 100rs..
Nice place to visit with family if u love Kerala food..

Improvement:Please include some good pieces of chicken in Biriyani too..')]

address: 941/1, Shop 4, Hulimavu Main Road, Bannerghatta Road, Bangalore
name: Bangalore Pantry
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated near Hulimavi hate, this has become our lunch spot as it's very close to college. Most of their food is good. It should be among the most pocket friendly places around here. Good food, service might get delayed during lunch hours as it gets very crowded.

Kerala porota is a must try here. Their veg n non-veg curries are all good. Chicken Hyderabadi Biryani is also a good option here. I like their chicken shawarma as well. Overall a good, pocket friendly restaurant.

I wouldn't recommend their malabari chicken biryani because is basically chicken mixed in ghee rice. Their Chinese menu is just decent. Also the Chinese main course I have tried, the chicken was very hard. Their juices tasted very good the first time I tried but later on it became too watery.")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I have been to this place two times since it opened near my place. The best part of this place is , it's a very small restaurant but the hospitality that you will receive here is just great. Price is also not very high here. But the taste of food is just lovely. All kind of Asian food you will get here. Being a very new member to the list of good restaurants of the town, I really hope it goes a long way in future."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I've been going to this eatery ever since it has opened, and there has been no break from going there.
Primary reason being their most competitive of prices, starting with my most favourite Chole bature for Rs 40/- only, honey chilli potatoes for Rs 60/- only and amazing honey chilli chicken for Rs 100, all of these come in very decent portions.
The hospitality of the staff is amazing and it's always good to come back and try from a plethora of Malaysian, Thai, Chinese cuisines.
One of my favourite are the Char Kwateaou noodles, which are flat noodles tossed in a wok for Rs 140 only.
Also try their fried ice cream and banana toffee for under 50 rs!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I visited the place just like that.. Never expected it would turn out to be one of my best visit. Ordered honey crispy French fries ? along with chicken momo.. Trust me.. address: 1304, Ground Floor, 9th Cross, 20th Main, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Baba Chatkora
dish_liked: Dal Makhani, Thali, Matka Lassi
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  As always my goto order chaap. New outlet in Jp nagar will give you a feel of north India with its beautiful ambiance and punjabi songs playing around. Super crowded in weekends. Should go early to block your seats.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened restaurant which deals with your craving for dal makhni. A dhaba but in an uptown style. The service is a bit slow, but the food and the kebabs are yummm. Also, the green chutney is worth licking your fingers. Nice place for a fam jam!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Newly opened in JP Nagar, this place is close to RV Dental college. We went on a lazy afternoon to check out this place. The ambience of this place is very nice, with decent staff ready to offer good service. Coming to food, the menu is simple yet good. From their lassi to their thali, everything is authentic Punjabi style.
Overall, would recommend you to try this place once. A good place to have decent food.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Baba Chatkora is one of the options in JP Nagar for rejoicing authentic North Indian delicacies.

Visited this place only on the second day of after they opened. The place is nicely done. Bollywood and Punjabi numbers played at the backdrop gives a nice vibe to the place.

The food was decent.
We ordered Matka Lassi, Dhabha style Paneer, Ghobi matar and Butter naan.
Expected more from the Dhabha style paneer but it was the same as you would get in any any other North Indian restaurant.
The Matka Lassi was really thick and tasted great but the portion was pretty small.

A decent option for family dining but a bit overpriced. When you have so many options nearby and when a customer is looking for places which offers great value for money or something exemplary, Baba Chatkora fails miserably on that regard.

Happy eating!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Yay! Baba Chatkora is in JP Nagar now. Everything about this place is splendid. The food, the ambiance, the friendly staff and of course the music.

We ordered:
Soya Chaaps
Kulcha
And paneer starters
Plus they have the winter special menu too, and the gajar ka halwa is en pointe!

If you are craving for North Indian delicacies, look no further.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  As I am a big fan of Burger, I was looking for perfect place to satisfy my taste, so i visited Wudfyr as i had read positive reviews. One of the finest Restaurant options in the city; i found Wudfyr is a perfect place as it serves wide variety of pizza, burgers, pasta etc with a delicious taste. The staff is generous, courteous and their manager is always at your help. As per his suggestion i decided to try the South Mafia Burger and i was happy with the decision. The Burger was delicious . A food with perfect mixture of taste and healthyness.
The location and the interior was too impressive. And yes last but not the least its a pocket friendly too....
5 star for the food and wow for the Staff Service.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  We went on a Tuesday evening .Not very much crowded .Nice sitting place .Every single item we ordered had great taste and presentation .Special mention to creamy cheese pasta ,Oreo surprise , Loaded nachos with cheesy sauce .Definitely worth visiting again if wanting to eat healthy food and snacks . 5 star for price and hygiene. 4.5 for food and service. Nice experience.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A (not so) hidden gem! Good ambience and wonderful food. While the menu is not exhaustive, what they serve is right up there in taste.
Great burgers with buns dipped in vegetable juice to give them their colours (red, black, etc.).
With the 25% discount offer they had going on, it was great value for money as well.')]
