reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Well it was a utter disaapointment. Not anger, just utter disappointment in the quality and quantity of food served. Has Bangaloreans reached such a point that they do not care about the food served.

First the good points:
The ambience was over the top. And that too in the hub of the city. 11/10 for ambience.
Price was reasonable.

Next the disappointments:
The soup was bland, the prawns were too salty and the fish was overcooked. Even the people on the other table returned the pizza due to bad taste.

If I ever go there again, it is just to sit for a few hours sipping a drink and take in the ambience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new microbrewery situated in JP nagar.As soon as you enter youÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ll be mesmerised by the ambience and the amount of space to dine.The in house brewery too is amazing.
The Caribbean sunset is the best pick in mocktails
For starters the crusted prawns and peri peri fries were spectacularly amazing ?
Loved this place and its definitely a must try
The staff is very friendly and welcoming
Ambience:5/5
Food:4/5
Overall:4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  New microbrewery in South Bangalore, I loved the place. Everything was so beautiful & mesmerizing. Ambience is just awesome and huge with different seating options. Amazing food with varieties of brewed beer. Ordered chicken pizza it was just awesome. Would love to visit this place again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is simply awesome and a must visit place
The staff is very friendly and the best thing is quick service
You have many options to choose your seats but that too during the weekdays, the ambience is also amazing.
Must visit place and itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s good to have such Place in JP nagar ??'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Brahma Brews is the new youth centred restaurant and microbrewery. The multiple seating areas are very diverse with their own aura. The whole establishment can probably house about 2000 people. The beers are great and food doesn't let you down. The assorted bruschetta [veg] doesn't have a lot of taste. The paneer ghee roast is exceptional and the paneer used was very soft. The mocktails are great here. The music must be louder as the voice of the people is louder than the music itself. All in all this is a great place to visit."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This huge property located in the heart of JP Nagar can host about 2k people in their different sections. The voluminous of the place makes it very attractive.
Tasted their 3 brews(wit, klosh, IPA) and was not a fan of it.
They have a huge spread of veg and non veg starters, tried the veg nachos, ghee roast panner and kurkure kabba. These starters were of good quantity and tasted good too. Would recommend the ghee roast.
All in all a great place with good service and superb food. Can improve on the brewed beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Unique starters and great ambience . I don't drink, but the guzzlers say the brew is gud, as for me the mock tails were really gud and the overall experience was relaxing and yet you could catch the beat and the feel of the brewery will really engulf you."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Another brewery for the thirsty people to find solace.... big place and various sitting arrangements and ambience. Being a vegetarian and teatoddler does not give much leeway with the options to offer. Started with broccoli soup which was pleasant but that u can't it anywhere as. The less said about the drumstick soup. The cheese balls and kurkure tikki lacked the flavour and taste. Not sure if I would be going there again and might stick to hakuna ma tata instead."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place.. the micro brewery serves freshly brewed beer. There needs to be more on the beer menu to offer though. The bar menu is good..
The service is quick... Food is also nice, although I would need to try out more dishes to give a robust feedback on food.
Huge seating space and the ambience is key differentiator.

All in all good place to hang out and have a few beers!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  New brew place in town. They didn't have many brew options as mentioned on the menu card. Great ambience. Food options were plenty. Their weizenbock beer was damn nice, must try. Although I wanted to try honey scotch ale, which was not available sadly. We also tried their black n blue cocktail which was okay. Rustica pizza was yum as usual. ?"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Brewery started on the 1st Feb.. crafted beer options in south Bangalore are on a rise..this one apparently is the biggest place at the moment.. huge crowd on weekends..its situated next to hakuna matata..
Their starts were perfectly cooked..chicken biryani may well become their USP..yeah..u must try that...

Seating chairs I felt were a bit wobbly and u might just fall off if u drink one too many..

Staff and service was found to be professional..
Some one who loves visiting new breweries has something to look forward for..
Hope they brew speciality beer else am just too bored to find the same options in every brewery
.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ok this place was creating a lot of buzz so decided to go.
Went there with 9 of my friends and had prior booking but still have to wait for more than half an hour.

Starting with the ambience it's extremely beautiful ? and have a separate corner for couples for candle light dinner.
Only thing that ruined the ambience was there music. As the place is so big but they don't have enough speakers so it results to a flop nightlife.

Don't have enough options in their food menu especially for vegetarians.

But definitely you should visit the place once for it's ambience and it's drinks which is great.

Moreover it's a place for dine."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Had been here on a sat night, a pretty huge place. But feels kind of isolated. They have only 4 beers as of now - Kolsch , IPA, Weizenbock and Belgian Wit. The Belgian wit and wizenbock we're good, Kolsch and IPA not up to the mark. Mushroom chilly fry as a starter is nice."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Got here on a saturday evening/night . Lovely ambience, service was quick . Sweet staff, beer n food was good . Loved the andhra chilli chicken . Huge place . Goood music . Candle light dinner tables were really nice .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One of a kind place in JP Nagar. Huge open space that's not on a rooftop, hard to find in Bangalore! Seating modules with different ambience spread over multiple blocks and levels, gives anyone the kind of space they want.

Service was top notch, very well attended by the staff and all orders were served pretty quick despite the huge crowd on a weekend night.

South Indian starters we tried are excellent. But the continental/fusion starters were average. 7 Spices, a chef special was a bit disappointment with the BBQ sauce overpowering spices. Andhra Chilly Chicken was excellent. They had 4 beers on tap. Belgian Wit was great. Weizenbock was excellent and perfect for the current cool weather. Kolsch was very average, felt a bit watered down with no aftertaste. IPA was not up to the mark, the next batches would improve may be."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  Ok this place was creating a lot of buzz so decided to go.
Went there with 9 of my friends and had prior booking but still have to wait for more than half an hour.

Starting with the ambience it's extremely beautiful ? and have a separate corner for couples for candle light dinner.
Only thing that ruined the ambience was there music. As the place is so big but they don't have enough speakers so it results to a flop nightlife.

Don't have enough options in their food menu especially for vegetarians.

But definitely you should visit the place once for it's ambience and it's drinks which is great.

Moreover it's a place for dine."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

The Belgian wit and wizenbock we're good, Kolsch and IPA not up to the mark. Mushroom chilly fry as a starter is nice."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Got here on a saturday evening/night . Lovely ambience, service was quick . Sweet staff, beer n food was good . Loved the andhra chilli chicken . Huge place . Goood music . Candle light dinner tables were really nice .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One of a kind place in JP Nagar. Huge open space that's not on a rooftop, hard to find in Bangalore! Seating modules with different ambience spread over multiple blocks and levels, gives anyone the kind of space they want.

Service was top notch, very well attended by the staff and all orders were served pretty quick despite the huge crowd on a weekend night.

South Indian starters we tried are excellent. But the continental/fusion starters were average. 7 Spices, a chef special was a bit disappointment with the BBQ sauce overpowering spices. Andhra Chilly Chicken was excellent. They had 4 beers on tap. Belgian Wit was great. Weizenbock was excellent and perfect for the current cool weather. Kolsch was very average, felt a bit watered down with no aftertaste. IPA was not up to the mark, the next batches would improve may be."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

name: Levitate Brewery and Kitchen
dish_liked: Wheat Beer, Tiramisu, Lager, Rustica Pizza, Paneer Lollipop, Chicken Peri Peri Kebab, Nachos

  Terribly expensive with extremely small portions on the starters. But the brews are absolutely stunning and knock outs. That and the killer terrace ambiance deserves this 4 star rating.

  What a wonderful place!!! 5 stars is very much deserved!!! Beautiful ambience!!! Tasty food and kick-ass beers!!! Over-all a lovely evening!!! Order anything there it's all lip smaking!!!   Perfect place for weekend lunch... IÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92m sure it looks beautiful in the evenings too though looking at the other pics but the open dining area is very spacious and just apt for a meal outside.. the food is amazing, friendly staff, valet parking available, great spot to click some nice pics, lovely ambience.. definitely recommend it..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls. 
Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.
 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

Everything was yummy here the best among these was Rava Upma cheese balls something new in the menu, broccoli 65 is a must try if you like broccoli and yes the french fries were super yummy. In drinks i liked their strawberry flavored mock tails and spicy guava.
 In deserts, you must have their cheesecake along with their special chocolate cake which was yummy. Also, the drinks are also very nice at Levitate Brewery & Kitchen and must try their cocktails!

address: 15, Bannerghatta Main Road, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Le Arabia
dish_liked: Chicken Biryani
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The quantity is more than enough, but the price does not quantify the quality. The rice was undercooked, so flavourless. Need to improve the taste and quality for sure'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Very good Arabian style restaurant and very awesome food and it's verities are approachable.
We usually go here for official lunch, also with a very good ambiance. Do visit here"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great ambiance and some great food but not the Arabian cuisine though. Rest, the food, service and ambiance is really good! Would recommend this place for some good food in and around J P Nagar'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Can this really be called an Arabian restaurant? No. The menu is mostly filled with typical Indian/Mughlai and Chinese dishes, and the Arabian share is limited to some barbecues. Honestly I was pretty disappointed with their barbecues. It was undercooked and missed the fire character. Though the marination was good, it tasted raw. Surprised that they served Rumali Roti as the side for barbecue instead of Kubboos or any Arabic bread, and the roti was hard and rubbery, inedible. Restaurants like Zaitoon and Fattoush serve absolutely delicious barbecues, even Empire would be a better choice. On the other hand, prawns were delicious and soft like silk.

Ambience is great. Neatly and tastefully done interiors. Pretty good for large groups and families. Service is very good too.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  If you have a craving for Middle Eastern delicacies, now your taste buds would find a justification at Least Arabia. Superb interiors and courteous attendants. The foods are great, specially, the Arabian Shawarma, Nawab Chicken and Irani Kebab are a must try.')]

address: 1304, Ground Floor, 9th Cross, 20th Main, JP Nagar, Bangalore
name: Baba Chatkora
dish_liked: Dal Makhani, Thali, Matka Lassi
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  As always my goto order chaap. New outlet in Jp nagar will give you a feel of north India with its beautiful ambiance and punjabi songs playing around. Super crowded in weekends. Should go early to block your seats.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A newly opened restaurant which deals with your craving for dal makhni. A dhaba but in an uptown style. The service is a bit slow, but the food and the kebabs are yummm. Also, the green chutney is worth licking your fingers. Nice place for a fam jam!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Newly opened in JP Nagar, this place is close to RV Dental college. We went on a lazy afternoon to check out this place. The ambience of this place is very nice, with decent staff ready to offer good service. Coming to food, the menu is simple yet good. From their lassi to their thali, everything is authentic Punjabi style.
Overall, would recommend you to try this place once. A good place to have decent food.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Baba Chatkora is one of the options in JP Nagar for rejoicing authentic North Indian delicacies.

Visited this place only on the second day of after they opened. The place is nicely done. Bollywood and Punjabi numbers played at the backdrop gives a nice vibe to the place.

The food was decent.
We ordered Matka Lassi, Dhabha style Paneer, Ghobi matar and Butter naan.
Expected more from the Dhabha style paneer but it was the same as you would get in any any other North Indian restaurant.
The Matka Lassi was really thick and tasted great but the portion was pretty small.

A decent option for family dining but a bit overpriced. When you have so many options nearby and when a customer is looking for places which offers great value for money or something exemplary, Baba Chatkora fails miserably on that regard.

Happy eating!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Yay! Baba Chatkora is in JP Nagar now. Everything about this place is splendid. The food, the ambiance, the friendly staff and of course the music.

We ordered:
Soya Chaaps
Kulcha
And paneer starters
Plus they have the winter special menu too, and the gajar ka halwa is en pointe!

If you are craving for North Indian delicacies, look no further.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  As I am a big fan of Burger, I was looking for perfect place to satisfy my taste, so i visited Wudfyr as i had read positive reviews. One of the finest Restaurant options in the city; i found Wudfyr is a perfect place as it serves wide variety of pizza, burgers, pasta etc with a delicious taste. The staff is generous, courteous and their manager is always at your help. As per his suggestion i decided to try the South Mafia Burger and i was happy with the decision. The Burger was delicious . A food with perfect mixture of taste and healthyness.
The location and the interior was too impressive. And yes last but not the least its a pocket friendly too....
5 star for the food and wow for the Staff Service.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  We went on a Tuesday evening .Not very much crowded .Nice sitting place .Every single item we ordered had great taste and presentation .Special mention to creamy cheese pasta ,Oreo surprise , Loaded nachos with cheesy sauce .Definitely worth visiting again if wanting to eat healthy food and snacks . 5 star for price and hygiene. 4.5 for food and service. Nice experience.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A (not so) hidden gem! Good ambience and wonderful food. While the menu is not exhaustive, what they serve is right up there in taste.
Great burgers with buns dipped in vegetable juice to give them their colours (red, black, etc.).
With the 25% discount offer they had going on, it was great value for money as well.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Best Kerala restaurant in the vicinity.Nice spacious interiors and good service.
Had chicken biriyani and Kerala meals..
While chicken biriyani was not bad,Kerala meals is very good.Their sambar,pachadi,beetroot pickle was out of the world.
Apart from the above they give payasam,upperi,rasam,pappadam,one veg side dish(got bhindi masala which was very good) and a good amount of rice...all for 100rs..
Nice place to visit with family if u love Kerala food..
I will be visiting again this time to try fried fish here'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Right on the Road side and easy to see..This place offers Great Chicken partials and chicken Dry Biriyani..these are my repeat Orders from This Place.

Also if you would like to try some awesome Kerala snacks like the banana fry and unnakaya then you should try this Place..Giving a 4* for the items we tried.

Improvement:Please include some good pieces of chicken in Biriyani too..')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Being a vegetarian foodie, I have tried most of the vegetarian friendly places in bangalore and this is a good addition to it.

This is a brand new restaurant which offers mostly Noth Indian food with fancy names.

Below are few items I tried:

1. House special Pani puri: Always loved Pani puri but the taste here was just average. A suggestion to give meetha with the paani.

2. Charcoal grilled babycorn: They were perfect with the right balance of crispyness and softness. Loved the mint chutney which came with the dish as well.

3. Spicy Indian: A Guava Chilli mocktail which was lip smacking and refreshing.

4. Paneer makhani with butter naan: I could have this over and over again... It was that good! The Paneer was cooked well and the gravy wasn't very sweet which was very delicious.

Overall, this restaurant has good vegetarian food and service is also fast. Costed 1k for 3 people with the Zomato gold option of 1+1 on food. Will definitely visit again to try more dishes here."), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED

  Cute little place with nice ambience and a fun theme. The soups were really tasty. The food was quite good, though some of the starters were really spicy. Tandoor broccoli was the best and we repeated the dish again. The humms dish was amazing too with really well made sauces of different kinds.
Tried biryani and Mexican chawal for main course and found it just okay. But the desserts picked up again and the pannacotta and tiramisu were different and fun'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place is now in my favourites list. Tried the China meets Churchgate Wonton, Thai style panneer kebab biryani, Malai Kofta Pasta and Filter Coffee Rasagula. Loved them all. Good ambience and courteous staff. This place is a must visit.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I had been here with a few friends to try out this new place a few days ago, and one of their owners informed us that it is a new place that has opened about 15 days ago. However, was extremely disappointed. This place is trying very hard to be different, but will fail miserably in the long run. The food was okayish in taste, and overpriced for the small quantity they are serving. 

For example, I have been to plenty of places where for the same price of an appetizer, I can get a quantity good enough for 2-3 people. 

Further, most of their appetizers we had are such that it can be made at home, better than what they make.

Soups were meh, and lacking in flavor. Again, quantity for the price we are paying here is a big issue.

Will not visit again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Had been to this place last week on a week day so it was not very crowded we could get the table easily. Another reason to go here was for Gold offer.

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's a nice brewry at nice location. Ambiance is awesome. Food taste is good, could ask for spicy levels. Beer is good. Must try.

A well spent evening with my dear ones. Must try once with your best pals or romantic dates. Music is not so loud, you can talk with each other comfortably. Check out my pics for more details. @management I hardly give 4 star, hope you maintain this standard. All the best!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Who ever thought that there would be a microbrewery in JP Nagar one day. This place is just amazing. If you guys have any plans or wanna go on a date, this is the place to be.
Located in JP Nagar 5th phase right next to Hakuna Matata and bang opposite cult fitness, this place is tough to miss.
The entrance itself has a huge gate, and on entering it looks like a mini city. They have ample of sitting place. Very clean, hygienic.
I must say the service the super fast even after catering to so many people.
Food is delicious. Drinks are Kickass. Beers are just perfect.
Whether it's indian or Italian cuisine, these guys excel in it.
Slightly on the pricey side but worth it.
Do try it out. Highly recommended place."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Well it was a utter disaapointment. Not anger, just utter disappointment in the quality and quantity of food served. Has Bangaloreans reached such a point that they do not care about the food served.

First the good points:
The ambience was over the top. And that too in the hub of the city. 11/10 for ambience.
Price was reasonable.

Next the disappointments:
The soup was bland, the prawns were too salty and the fish was overcooked. Even the people on the other table returned the pizza due to bad taste.

If I ever go there again, it is just to sit for a few hours sipping a drink and take in the ambience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A new microbrewery situated in JP nagar.As soon as you enter youÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92ll be mesmerised by the ambience and the amount of space to dine.The in house brewery too is amazing.
The Caribbean sunset is the best pick in mocktails
For starters the crusted prawns and peri peri fries were spectacularly amazing ?
Loved this place and its definitely a must try
The staff is very friendly and welcoming
Ambience:5/5
Food:4/5
Overall:4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  New microbrewery in South Bangalore, I loved the place. Everything was so beautiful & mesmerizing. Ambience is just awesome and huge with different seating options. Amazing food with varieties of brewed beer. Ordered chicken pizza it was just awesome. Would love to visit this place again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is simply awesome and a must visit place
The staff is very friendly and the best thing is quick service
You have many options to choose your seats but that too during the weekdays, the ambience is also amazing.
Must visit place and itÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s good to have such Place in JP nagar ??'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Brahma Brews is the new youth centred restaurant and microbrewery. The multiple seating areas are very diverse with their own aura. The whole establishment can probably house about 2000 people. The beers are great and food doesn't let you down. The assorted bruschetta [veg] doesn't have a lot of taste. The paneer ghee roast is exceptional and the paneer used was very soft. The mocktails are great here. The music must be louder as the voice of the people is louder than the music itself. All in all this is a great place to visit."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This huge property located in the heart of JP Nagar can host about 2k people in their different sections. The voluminous of the place makes it very attractive.
Tasted their 3 brews(wit, klosh, IPA) and was not a fan of it.
They have a huge spread of veg and non veg starters, tried the veg nachos, ghee roast panner and kurkure kabba. These starters were of good quantity and tasted good too. Would recommend the ghee roast.
All in all a great place with good service and superb food. Can improve on the brewed beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Unique starters and great ambience . I don't drink, but the guzzlers say the brew is gud, as for me the mock tails were really gud and the overall experience was relaxing and yet you could catch the beat and the feel of the brewery will really engulf you."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Another brewery for the thirsty people to find solace.... big place and various sitting arrangements and ambience. Being a vegetarian and teatoddler does not give much leeway with the options to offer. Started with broccoli soup which was pleasant but that u can't it anywhere as. The less said about the drumstick soup. The cheese balls and kurkure tikki lacked the flavour and taste. Not sure if I would be going there again and might stick to hakuna ma tata instead."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place.. the micro brewery serves freshly brewed beer. There needs to be more on the beer menu to offer though. The bar menu is good..
The service is quick... Food is also nice, although I would need to try out more dishes to give a robust feedback on food.
Huge seating space and the ambience is key differentiator.

All in all good place to hang out and have a few beers!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  New brew place in town. They didn't have many brew options as mentioned on the menu card. Great ambience. Food options were plenty. Their weizenbock beer was damn nice, must try. Although I wanted to try honey scotch ale, which was not available sadly. We also tried their black n blue cocktail which was okay. Rustica pizza was yum as usual. ?"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Brewery started on the 1st Feb.. crafted beer options in south Bangalore are on a rise..this one apparently is the biggest place at the moment.. huge crowd on weekends..its situated next to hakuna matata..
Their starts were perfectly cooked..chicken biryani may well become their USP..yeah..u must try that...

Seating chairs I felt were a bit wobbly and u might just fall off if u drink one too many..

Staff and service was found to be professional..
Some one who loves visiting new breweries has something to look forward for..
Hope they brew speciality beer else am just too bored to find the same options in every brewery
.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Ok this place was creating a lot of buzz so decided to go.
Went there with 9 of my friends and had prior booking but still have to wait for more than half an hour.

Starting with the ambience it's extremely beautiful ? and have a separate corner for couples for candle light dinner.
Only thing that ruined the ambience was there music. As the place is so big but they don't have enough speakers so it results to a flop nightlife.

Don't have enough options in their food menu especially for vegetarians.

But definitely you should visit the place once for it's ambience and it's drinks which is great.

Moreover it's a place for dine."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  Got here on a saturday evening/night . Lovely ambience, service was quick . Sweet staff, beer n food was good . Loved the andhra chilli chicken . Huge place . Goood music . Candle light dinner tables were really nice .'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  One of a kind place in JP Nagar. Huge open space that's not on a rooftop, hard to find in Bangalore! Seating modules with different ambience spread over multiple blocks and levels, gives anyone the kind of space they want.

Service was top notch, very well attended by the staff and all orders were served pretty quick despite the huge crowd on a weekend night.

South Indian starters we tried are excellent. But the continental/fusion starters were average. 7 Spices, a chef special was a bit disappointment with the BBQ sauce overpowering spices. Andhra Chilly Chicken was excellent. They had 4 beers on tap. Belgian Wit was great. Weizenbock was excellent and perfect for the current cool weather. Kolsch was very average, felt a bit watered down with no aftertaste. IPA was not up to the mark, the next batches would improve may be."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A spacious brewery, A much needed requirement in JP Nagar. A perfect place to chill post office hours & a weekend with friends. People dont need to travel far for having fresh brews.
This place is full of greenery, water bodies (such as fountain & pond). The staff is very courteous, the food is lip smacking. We tried a lot of dishes, from veg to non veg, everything was up-to the mark including the presentation & taste. And wil recommend other as well to visit"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Nice place! I got a feeling of it being sort of a 'resort' than a pub. Its huge, spacious with a lot of open area and has various sections of seating, it even gave me an impression like the place could never appear crowded even if it were filled to capacity- which I doubt could happen as theres so much seating space that there could always be room to accomodate guests even if it were a weekend. We for instance had plenty of seating options to choose from, we chose one near the pool. Ordered for Chicken Nachos which had generous amount of meat in it and tasted fine. The Jerk Chicken I think should have been accompanied with some interesting dips to go with, it tasted pretty plain to me. The pizza Polloala Griglia was good. Finally the dessert 'Chocolate Surprise' was pretty inventive but I didn't fall for the Indian Sweet Meat + Chocolate combination. It was overall a good experience because the ambience is simply lovely- classy infact to also bring families into. Recommend it."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Most points are for the ambience. The place is huge with various seating options ranging from group hangout to romantic.

  A new brewery has come up in JP Nagar with 3 floors of sitting, it has a lovely rooftop ambiance which has a really nice view. The service and staff are really good here and as for the food I have no words, it was just great!
 I tried the tandoori mushroom, veg Manchurian, broccoli 65, veg farmhouse pizza, tulsi paneer, Vietnamese french fries, Rava Upma cheese balls.

name: Kapoor's Punjabi Rolls
dish_liked: Rolls, Veggie Roll, Paneer Achari Roll, Keema Roll
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One word for them i.e. Impeccable.A cute little outlet situated in HRBR layout.Its worth every penny you pay them.They offer punjabi rolls and masala Cold drinks , They do have a discount for group as well .if you are looking for quick bites it is place to go for.

I tried

1.Punjabi Style cheese Roll :- It is fully laden with Amul cheese and a great combination of veggies and sauces.I would definitely recommend this one.

2. Baingan Bhartha roll :- If you are nostalgic about how your mom made bhartha.Do try this one because they were nearest to.that taste .

3. Paneer Achari Roll :- This is must if you are a paneer lover.If comes with a twist of achaari flavour to tickle your taste bud.

They can improvise a bit on soft drinks but at this price in Bangalore,it's great.

Taste -4.5/5
Texture -4/5
Presentation- 4/5
Service:-5/5
Ambience -4/5"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This gem of a place is located opposite to Barbeque Nation in Kalyan Nagar and easy to notice from moving vehicle. It has colorful and bright upscale interior and seating for 20 people.

It offers proper Punjabi Style rolls, literally Punjabi Style, where butter is used Dil kholke and they have tried to keep everything as authentic as possible which means lots of pure Amul butter and masala's which are used in all the outlets are made only by head Chef of Kapoor's Cafe to ensure consistency in taste and quality.

They offer 12 varieties of rolls which includes Paneer, Mashroom, Achari, Baigan Bharta, Aloo Matar, Bindi Do Pyaza Cheese and Veggies.
It's a pure vegetarian place and I think it's the only place in Bangalore which offers so many delicious varieties of rolls under one roof.

It's a must try place for all the veggetarian foodies and they also deliver food through all the leading platforms such as Zomato, Swiggy and Uber Eats."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  It's a place to remember mom's made rolls for lunch every other day so now there is a alternative for it u can head to this place for some amazing rolls especially in VEG (My fav)...witnessed variety of them here all of them were splendid and lovely (my personal Fav - Bhindi roll)
.
And also cheese roll is yummy cheeselicious ???

Second fav was ALOO MATAR well they also had veg keema roll do try as many as u can it will be worth the money u spend also worth u r time if u r visting this cozy outlet with a feel of (apna adda mein chalte hain) ?"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Newly opened roll joint is party of the famous Kapoors Cafe franchose. I'm sure lots need to improve starting with Menu and most importantly service and presentation. Currently it's half and half. Quality need to improve for sure and I know you guys can. Looking forward."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Who says rolls are not meant for vegetarian??? Kapoor?s cafe and rolls is the answer for all your statements!
So they have come up with a new idea of vegetarian rolls stuffed with different flavours more specifically paneer , cheese , veg keema , bhindi ,allooo matar and so much more !
Wait! They have masala soda which you can have it with these rolls .
This gave me a homely feeling while eating cheese and bhindi masala rolls I literally felt nostalgic.
You should definitely try these and share your experiences! Kudos to the team and wishing them all the best \U0001f970'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This place was on our list from last couple of months. We were excited as it belonged to kapoor's Cafe. The place nice small inside. The ambience is colourful. reviews_list: [('Rated 1.0', 'RATED\n  I understand Zomato says give positive comments for the restaurants that are reviewed. I will definitely not be visiting or ordering from this place ever.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED\n  Pathetic. The pizza recipe used here is horrible. The pizza base tastes like a pastry crust. A wood fire pizza takes max 2 minutes in the oven. This one took well over 15 minutes. The chef took the pizza out midway, poked the bubbles with a knife and topped it with more cheese and put it back inside again. The quality of the cheese was also questionable. what a blunder ordering here. That pizza I paid 200 Rs was worth only 30 Rs.')]

[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  For a Saturday lunch, I ordered some quality junkies from D-Zaprino. The delivery was pretty fast, and talking about the package, it was good. The good thing about it was, the food was delivered hot, and that made my pizza delivery experience even better. I ordered,

Veggie Nuggets,
Chilli Cheese Burger Combo,
OMG Cheese Pizza.

address: 507, 4th Cross, 2nd Block, CMR Road, HRBR Layout, Kalyan Nagar, Bangalore
name: Kapoor's Punjabi Rolls
dish_liked: Rolls, Veggie Roll, Paneer Achari Roll, Keema Roll
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  One word for them i.e. Impeccable.A cute little outlet situated in HRBR layout.Its worth every penny you pay them.They offer punjabi rolls and masala Cold drinks , They do have a discount for group as well .if you are looking for quick bites it is place to go for.

I tried

1.Punjabi Style cheese Roll :- It is fully laden with Amul cheese and a great combination of veggies and sauces.I would definitely recommend this one.

2. Baingan Bhartha roll :- If you are nostalgic about how your mom made bhartha.Do try this one because they were nearest to.that taste .

3. Paneer Achari Roll :- This is must if you are a paneer lover.If comes with a twist of achaari flavour to tickle your taste bud.

They can improvise a bit on soft drinks but at this price in Bangalore,it's great.

Taste -4.5/5
Texture -4/5
Presentation- 4/5
Service:-5/5
Ambience -4/5"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This gem of a place is located opposite to Barbeque Nation in Kalyan Nagar and easy to notice from moving vehicle. It has colorful and bright upscale interior and seating for 20 people.

It offers proper Punjabi Style rolls, literally Punjabi Style, where butter is used Dil kholke and they have tried to keep everything as authentic as possible which means lots of pure Amul butter and masala's which are used in all the outlets are made only by head Chef of Kapoor's Cafe to ensure consistency in taste and quality.

They offer 12 varieties of rolls which includes Paneer, Mashroom, Achari, Baigan Bharta, Aloo Matar, Bindi Do Pyaza Cheese and Veggies.
It's a pure vegetarian place and I think it's the only place in Bangalore which offers so many delicious varieties of rolls under one roof.

It's a must try place for all the veggetarian foodies and they also deliver food through all the leading platforms such as Zomato, Swiggy and Uber Eats."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  It's a place to remember mom's made rolls for lunch every other day so now there is a alternative for it u can head to this place for some amazing rolls especially in VEG (My fav)...witnessed variety of them here all of them were splendid and lovely (my personal Fav - Bhindi roll)
.
And also cheese roll is yummy cheeselicious ???

Second fav was ALOO MATAR well they also had veg keema roll do try as many as u can it will be worth the money u spend also worth u r time if u r visting this cozy outlet with a feel of (apna adda mein chalte hain) ?"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Newly opened roll joint is party of the famous Kapoors Cafe franchose. I'm sure lots need to improve starting with Menu and most importantly service and presentation. Currently it's half and half. Quality need to improve for sure and I know you guys can. Looking forward."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Who says rolls are not meant for vegetarian??? KapoorÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s cafe and rolls is the answer for all your statements!
So they have come up with a new idea of vegetarian rolls stuffed with different flavours more specifically paneer , cheese , veg keema , bhindi ,allooo matar and so much more !
Wait! They have masala soda which you can have it with these rolls .
This gave me a homely feeling while eating cheese and bhindi masala rolls I literally felt nostalgic.
You should definitely try these and share your experiences! Kudos to the team and wishing them all the best \U0001f970'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This place was on our list from last couple of months. We were excited as it belonged to kapoor's Cafe. The place nice small inside. The ambience is colourful. The sitting arrangements are too small for family of three (two adults and one kid to sit on one table). Its really conjusted. The menu is limited with 12 rolls, which is good. We had Hara Bhara Kebab Roll and Kadai Paneer Roll. Both tasted yumm and delicious. The presentation was just perfect. Few disappointments, they don't serve water, they don't cut and serve Rolls in a plate!! Rating it 3 coz of space, water and plates issues. Taste of the Rolls are perfect. Try once.")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have admitted my mom in a reputed hospital in Jayanagar where outside food is strictly not allowed and their canteen closes by 9:30 PM. My home is in Whitefield. Almost after 1:30 hrs journey I reached the hospital by 10:00 PM. I was super hungry. Around 10:30 only I started searching for food in Zomato, I don?t want to eat heavy but want something hot and steamed. What would be a better choice than momos? So, found this Momo Blues! Ordered both momo blues oz and shrimp momos - I was totally surprised by the quality and taste of the momos. The momos were really steaming hot and soft. Even in many big restaurants, the momos I had were hard and dry! These momos tasted fresh and juicy... if you are staying in and around of Koramangala and if you are a momo lover, then your go-to place is momo blues! Their shrimp momos worth the every penny! They were perfect as well!
Thanks to Zomato?s delivery guy! He came real quick and saved me from my hunger!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's a small kiosk right next to potato bae, and it's easy to miss.
We tried the Veg Jhol Momo's and it was good. The price was higher according to the quantity (6 pcs for 110 bucks) , but I'll give them a 4 for the effort.
Also, if they had few more options for Veg Momo's, it would've been great.")]

dish_liked: Ulavacharu, Biryani, Rajugari Kodi Pulao, Bangla Kodi, Curd Rice, Gadwal Kodi Pulao, Fish
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu opened its doors in Blore after a successful run in Hyderabad. We went here for dinner & on recommendation by the manager ordered Korameenu Vepudu, Konaseema Mamsam Vepudu & Kodi Raju gari polao & Apricot delight(best of the lot) in desserts I loved the food..no complaints. But the service is bit confusing. They need to brush up their skills of serving in a restaurant at peak hours specially. I did not quite like the ambiance also reminded of Durga Puja Theme pandals back home. Pricing is a bit high compared to quantity served. Will visit again to try their unique variety of biryani & polao'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had been yesterday to this amazing place with friends over lunch.. They had the food served in banana leaf for the 1st time since it opened. We ordered Konaseema Kodi Vepudu and Bamboo Chicken as non veg starters and Mokkajoanna Vepudu (Baby Corn dish) as veg starter.. The bamboo chicken was spicy to the likes of everyone. Distinct bamboo flavour takes the dish to different level.. For mains, we took Ulavacharu Kodi pulao, Dal fry, rotis and Veg salad.. They were very good..

I would highly recommend this place to all if they want to try Authentic Andhra food..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Last week visited Ulavacharu with my friends. Food taste and quality were pretty decent except desserts.

Service was not impressive. We asked them politely to wait for serving until we finish but they were in urgency to serve food.

Ambience is quite different and good.

Ratings:
Food: 4/5
Quality: 4/5
Service:3/5
Ambience: 3.5/5'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  A typical Andhra reasturant like all the other reasturant, the ambience is not that great , it's got a raw feel, but doens't seem exciting , the food was like any other Andhra reasturant , nothing different. The customer service is pretty average, pricing is way too high.. it's like any other Andhra reasturant.."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Visited ulavacharu with lot of expectations and ended up getting badly disappointed. The pulav we ordered were not living up to the Andhra style taste. The konaseema kodi and other side dishes dint taste good either and the quantity given was too less . Even the pappu charu annam tasted bad . Neither did the servers knew what they were serving . Definitely won't recommend it ."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I need to explore this place more. My first experience was not so great. We ordered Raju kodi biryani. Rice was sticky, there were rice lumps and pieces were hard and bland.
Got it replaced with Mutton biryani and it was just normal biryani.
I would say its on the pricy side atleast by 50 bucks.
Ambience is rustic and reminds of rural set up and Granny's house.
I somehow feel they are really good at what they are preparing, i just need to explore more or go at the right time."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  What a brilliant place \U0001f929 let's get straight to the food. I had Telangana mamsam Kura and kulcha. It was like a marriage made in heaven. The mutton was brilliantly cooked, the gravy was so flavourful. I cannot stop gushing about how brilliant it was. A little bit too oily, no doubt. But it hit all the right notes!

I also tried the uluvacharu Kodi pulao.. the biriyani was definitely good but nothing extraordinary. Definitely going back there for more!

A small feedback would be to also explain the various dishes that you have since the entire menu has the Telugu names. It would be easier for the customers to understand what they're ordering."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It was my first time visit to the place and trust me I was awestruck with the entrance and then with the interior but the food was as tasty as the entrance and the stuff being so polite and asking for your comfort zone and making you explain the food items as the menu for the north indian to understand is difficult. The way the atmosphere they have maintained is beautiful and the Manager. Suresh was excellent at the service he suggested us the best spicy biryani - Gadwal Kodi Pulao and we ordered it and damn yummmmmy!! Infact I took one parcel to send to my city surat,gujarat with a friend next day and it still dint get spoilt. However we ordered three parcel but they were out of stock :( so had to send just one. But beautiful experience and not too pricy. Thank you for everything!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Koramangala has new destination for another Authentic cusine and its Ualavacharu. Its opened in the prime location and easy to find. Their Ambience is mind blowing. Starting from the entrance to every corner the decoration is very well pictured. They are 2 branches in Hyderabad and this is their 1st branch in Bangalore.

Coming to food, I loved Raju gari kodi pulav- which was little gravish, spicy and is different from any other biryanis.

For starters we ordered Kona seema kodi vepudu- which is semi gravy and fiery. Chapala Vepudu was crispy and good.

Main course we took Roti along Andhra Kodi curry which was spicy and had fine taste. Gadwal Kodi pulao was good in taste. Apricot Delight desert is a must try.

All the food are spicy and this would an irresistible place for Andhra cuisine lovers. Will definitely mark this place for Andhra meal next time. Worth trying. !'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Another badly wanted to go restaurant with lot of expectations. It was a Saturday evening and this was a new place in town. The interiors of this place is very good and we were pretty impressed with the variety of pulao/biryani options we could see on the menu.

We did ordered almost three different pulao and starters. The Andra style starters were good to start with and than comes the biryani. The presentation of the biryani was good but the biryani?s were not up-to the badge. What started with good experience ended with a satisfactory note.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu is the new Andhra speciality restaurant which has recently opened up in Kormangala,Bangalore.
The decor is done beautifully with Lord Krishna idol,stone pillars,wooden waterfall structure and a whole lot of comfortable seatings.
Being a south Indian I absolutely love Andhra flavours which is spicy and laced with richness of ghee.just the way I like it ?
I personally loved the Ulvacharu,Bangla Kodi,Konaseema Kodi Vepudu,Raju Gari Kodi Pulav.
Do visit this legendary place which is famous in Hyderabad and now serving delicacies in Bengaluru?

thegalwhoblogs.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ulavacharu the restuarant which brings the finest delicacies of andhra prsdesh to our own Koramangala.

Ulavacharu itself a dish prepared from horse grame which is very famous in Andhra Pradesh.

Rustic Ambience which gives you the feel of old homes in village.

Welcoming Indian desserts were
Khaja and badusha.

Bangla Kodi a uniquely prepared dish where boneless chicken stuffed in a potato pockets.

The food was amazing especially Raju Gari kodi pulao.

And Kona Seema Kodi vepudu this was the spiciest chicken Starter I had here.

The gutti vankaya pulao this was amazing.

Tandoori fish don't miss out this guy's it's a must have here.A full size koramenu cooked with right amount of masala.

Apricot delight a very popular sweet dish of Hyderabad made with apricot and served with cream.
This was a bliss as always desserts are love."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  After a long and successful stint at Hyderabad, the birthplace of Andhra Cuisine, this restaurant now serves Bangaloreans with the same awesome cuisine that Hyderabadis have enjoyed for sometime.
The dishes here are prepared quite well and taste good.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ulavacharu has arrived in bangalore! Located next to empire koramangala, near to jnc College. This road is like Food capital for bangalore. Ulavacharu is right on location. I had heard of this restaurant which has some unique dishes in its menu. Ambience is quite good with soothing decors. I ordered their signature dish rajugari kodi palav, Bangla kodi. They gave rava laddu as complimentary which tasted excellent. Bangla kodi was crispy, but few pieces of chicken were chewy which they can work on. I am sure they will. Raju Gari kodi palav is one of its kind, it was flavourful, kind of semi gravy, tasted really good. Palav was really hot when they served had to wait for some time before I got started, chicken pieces were tender and juicy. The raitha went well with the palav. Service is efficient. Overall ulavacharu is here to make a mark.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Ulavacharu's inception is an effort towards attending a void that was prevalent in every metropolitan decorated with multi cuisines and themed restaurants. Our team from Wanna Know Where We Eat? stepped in to experience the bliss, taste, tradition and flavour of Ulavacharu today and are still in the hangover of the taste and tradition that they offered us. We rate this place 4.8/5.0 after evaluating all the 25 factors that we consider before rating a restaurant. The experience we had over there was next to perfection and the food served over there was a pure bliss.")]

  Seven Ate Nine is a place who thinks local, cook local. Simple dishes made with great ingredients & special preparation with love is the USP of this place. We tried:

-Wasabi Malai Cheese Broccoli

-Soy Chilli

-Garlic Cheesy Bread

-Potato Wedges

-Crispy BBQ Corn

-Tandoori Mushroom & Jalapeno Naanizza

-Paneer Ghee Roast Burger

-Rasmali Tresleches

Naanizza & Ghee Roast Paneer Burger were too good & a must try. They provide shakes as well with different flavors which complements the food very well. The staff was quite prompt in serving hot & delicious food.

I feel totally satisfied for a value for money experience. Highly recommended. #ashishbansalfoodie

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Zomato should really start this decimal value for rating!
Anyway, this is a newly opened cafe at HSR. You can almost miss it, but shouldn't!
A cosy cafe tucked in a corner,away from the hustle. They were playing such soothing songs.
We had ordered schezwan idli (quite spicy, it has to be!), cheese garlic toast with salsa (also I didn't understand why garlic toast was priced the same), hibiscus tea ( soooo relaxing, it came with a sandwatch). They will ask for refilling as well. Also, we had lemongrass chai served in a kettle.
See, I would say it is a bit overpriced. But then they were giving 50% off over ?700 bill which is okay, but for 1 or 2 persons it would be difficult to reach that bill amount.
Overall,
Food 4/5
Service 4/5
Ambiance 4/5
VFM 3/5"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The ambience is top notch in this place. If you're a quiet person and would want some time to yourself, while you read a book and get some garam chai, this is the place for you. Their tea isn't other worldly great, but it's served in the cutest way possible and the pakoras are fine. The ambience, though, kills it.")]

  I have never had so many different kinds of chicken and all so tasty in one night ever before! You must try their sesame chicken, Chicken Tikka, Afghani Chicken and thin crust Pizzas!

Eye catching location, Amazing food, nice ambience and good music, they have it all!Their drinks are mind blowingly smooth and very well decorated!

  Well say hello to this new kid in the block when you wanna have a drinks night or hang out with your friends for sheesha..

The signature cocktails are amazing and u recommend the white rum and jaggery cocktail, best out of the lot.

For the food options, the place serves everything from finger food to pizza to Indian mains.

To finger point i had the most amazing Aglio Olio here when I have never liked it anywhere in the past.

The pizzas are thin crust and straight out of the woodfired oven. Also they serve the double layer pizzas which doubles your happu. Must try...

Starters are really nice and has extensive spread to go with the drinks.

In mains i liked hakka noodles, paneer makhani served with saffron rice which is prepared on point.

  What a great experience this turned out to be. Khichiya is a delectable, yummilicious snack food- a twist on tradition that's both healthy and tasty, without being weird.

  Not every often I give out 5 stars to a place but this place deserves every bit of it!

Try out this place to believe it!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Have had normal chicken momo and chicken jhol momo here in Momo blues. These ones are the closest to home. Love their jhol momo - just hope that it was a little more affordable. They don?t have a seating area which is a bit of a let down but it works out as long as the food is good. :)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have admitted my mom in a reputed hospital in Jayanagar where outside food is strictly not allowed and their canteen closes by 9:30 PM. My home is in Whitefield. Almost after 1:30 hrs journey I reached the hospital by 10:00 PM. I was super hungry. Around 10:30 only I started searching for food in Zomato, I don?t want to eat heavy but want something hot and steamed. What would be a better choice than momos? So, found this Momo Blues! Ordered both momo blues oz and shrimp momos - I was totally surprised by the quality and taste of the momos. The momos were really steaming hot and soft. Even in many big restaurants, the momos I had were hard and dry! These momos tasted fresh and juicy... if you are staying in and around of Koramangala and if you are a momo lover, then your go-to place is momo blues! Their shrimp momos worth the every penny! They were perfect as well!
Thanks to Zomato?s delivery guy! He came real quick and saved me from my hunger!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's a small kiosk right next to potato bae, and it's easy to miss.
We tried the Veg Jhol Momo's and it was good. The price was higher according to the quantity (6 pcs for 110 bucks) , but I'll give them a 4 for the effort.
Also, if they had few more options for Veg Momo's, it would've been great.")]

  What a great experience this turned out to be. Khichiya is a delectable, yummilicious snack food- a twist on tradition that's both healthy and tasty, without being weird.

The owner was very sweet and explained me all the variants available and how they put it together. Khichiyas are basically a healthy papad with sumptuous toppings from Gujarati/Jain/Rajasthani and other cuisines. There's also a Mexican Khichiya, which looks like a pizza on papad (!), cheese et all.

I'll be coming back for more !"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I have never had so many different kinds of chicken and all so tasty in one night ever before! You must try their sesame chicken, Chicken Tikka, Afghani Chicken and thin crust Pizzas!

Eye catching location, Amazing food, nice ambience and good music, they have it all!Their drinks are mind blowingly smooth and very well decorated!

With great starters to lip smacking well presented desserts, closed seating to Bangalore's windy open seating for hookah lovers, they have it all!??\U0001f91f?This place has started on a high note\U0001f929!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Well say hello to this new kid in the block when you wanna have a drinks night or hang out with your friends for sheesha..

The signature cocktails are amazing and u recommend the white rum and jaggery cocktail, best out of the lot.

For the food options, the place serves everything from finger food to pizza to Indian mains.

To finger point i had the most amazing Aglio Olio here when I have never liked it anywhere in the past.

The pizzas are thin crust and straight out of the woodfired oven. Also they serve the double layer pizzas which doubles your happu. Must try...

Starters are really nice and has extensive spread to go with the drinks.

In mains i liked hakka noodles, paneer makhani served with saffron rice which is prepared on point.

For desserts, we tried their chocolate walnut brownie served with vanilla ice cream. The brownie is cooked with perfection.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Food and sheesha were on point although the pricing and tax structure was on the higher side which wasnÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t communicated earlier!
Apart from that, no complaints!

  Have had normal chicken momo and chicken jhol momo here in Momo blues. These ones are the closest to home. Love their jhol momo - just hope that it was a little more affordable. They donÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t have a seating area which is a bit of a let down but it works out as long as the food is good. :)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I have admitted my mom in a reputed hospital in Jayanagar where outside food is strictly not allowed and their canteen closes by 9:30 PM. My home is in Whitefield. Almost after 1:30 hrs journey I reached the hospital by 10:00 PM. I was super hungry. Around 10:30 only I started searching for food in Zomato, I donÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92t want to eat heavy but want something hot and steamed. What would be a better choice than momos? So, found this Momo Blues! Ordered both momo blues oz and shrimp momos - I was totally surprised by the quality and taste of the momos. The momos were really steaming hot and soft. Even in many big restaurants, the momos I had were hard and dry! These momos tasted fresh and juicy... if you are staying in and around of Koramangala and if you are a momo lover, then your go-to place is momo blues! Their shrimp momos worth the every penny! address: 448, Jharana, 4th Sector, 17th Main, 17th Cross, Ground Floor, HSR Layout, Bangalore
name: Tea Trails
reviews_list:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Today I reviewed this place and Mark my words I was disappointed to the most extreme. To start with ambience, it was stinking of over fried oil. There was a strong smell of burnt oil all over the place.
Next comes the service of staff it was least as expected. There was only one person who wasn't able to handle many orders which was obvious.
I ordered Poha , That was a disastrous one. Half cooked without proper taste .
I ordered five spices chai and that was another bad dish . Now for tea you say water to milk content is mattered but how many of you would like to have coffee which is almost watered milk.
My overall experience was really bad .
Food : 1/5
Ambience : -1/5"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Zomato should really start this decimal value for rating!
Anyway, this is a newly opened cafe at HSR. You can almost miss it, but shouldn't!
A cosy cafe tucked in a corner,away from the hustle. They were playing such soothing songs.
We had ordered schezwan idli (quite spicy, it has to be!), cheese garlic toast with salsa (also I didn't understand why garlic toast was priced the same), hibiscus tea ( soooo relaxing, it came with a sandwatch). They will ask for refilling as well. Also, we had lemongrass chai served in a kettle.
See, I would say it is a bit overpriced. But then they were giving 50% off over ?700 bill which is okay, but for 1 or 2 persons it would be difficult to reach that bill amount.
Overall,
Food 4/5
Service 4/5
Ambiance 4/5
VFM 3/5"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The ambience is top notch in this place. If you're a quiet person and would want some time to yourself, while you read a book and get some garam chai, this is the place for you. Their tea isn't other worldly great, but it's served in the cutest way possible and the pakoras are fine. The ambience, though, kills it.")]

  What a great experience this turned out to be. Khichiya is a delectable, yummilicious snack food- a twist on tradition that's both healthy and tasty, without being weird.

The owner was very sweet and explained me all the variants available and how they put it together. Khichiyas are basically a healthy papad with sumptuous toppings from Gujarati/Jain/Rajasthani and other cuisines. There's also a Mexican Khichiya, which looks like a pizza on papad (!), cheese et all.

I'll be coming back for more !"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I have never had so many different kinds of chicken and all so tasty in one night ever before! You must try their sesame chicken, Chicken Tikka, Afghani Chicken and thin crust Pizzas!

Eye catching location, Amazing food, nice ambience and good music, they have it all!Their drinks are mind blowingly smooth and very well decorated!

With great starters to lip smacking well presented desserts, closed seating to Bangalore's windy open seating for hookah lovers, they have it all!??\U0001f91f?This place has started on a high note\U0001f929!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Well say hello to this new kid in the block when you wanna have a drinks night or hang out with your friends for sheesha..

The signature cocktails are amazing and u recommend the white rum and jaggery cocktail, best out of the lot.

For the food options, the place serves everything from finger food to pizza to Indian mains.

To finger point i had the most amazing Aglio Olio here when I have never liked it anywhere in the past.

The pizzas are thin crust and straight out of the woodfired oven. Also they serve the double layer pizzas which doubles your happu. Must try...

Starters are really nice and has extensive spread to go with the drinks.

In mains i liked hakka noodles, paneer makhani served with saffron rice which is prepared on point.

For desserts, we tried their chocolate walnut brownie served with vanilla ice cream. The brownie is cooked with perfection.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Apart from that, no complaints!
P.S. I loved their Chocolate Shake! Recommended'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.
Greek salad - Lettuce, Olives and Feta Cheese in the perfect mix.
Vergin Fried chicken - Chicken Fried with a coated batter. Tasted good.
Mix sause pasta - Penne Rigate Pasta with chicken cubes in a mixed sauce.
3 cheese pesto pizza - Generous servings of Cheddar, Parmesan and Mozarella Cheese layered on the Thin crust Pizza base tasted really well. You could feel the Cheese in every bite.
Chicken wrap - Chicken Cubes with veggies wrapped in Arabian Bread.
Chicken Nachos - Julienned chicken pieces and cheesw spread on Crisp Nachos.
Chicken pot rice - Jasmine rice with a mild Green Curry Gravy with veggies. Very flavourful and tasty.
Prawns kudla de Fogg - A preparation similar to the Prawns Ghee Roast with a similar texture and taste.
Excellent service and good food. Had a pleasant experience.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

address: 20/21, 20th Main Road, 1st Cross, Maruti Nagar Main Road, BTM, Bangalore
name: Choco Cheese
dish_liked: Waffles, Banana Nutella Crepe, Oreo Shake
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Well if are a waffle lover , then this is the place ..great waffles . Crunchy , proper fillings not over doing with sprinkles or artificial subtances.. has got lot of variants . Found mango , strawberry, blueberries etc on the menu. Menu is Damm exciting and a must try for all.
We tried Choco Drizzle and Peanut Butter Strawberry and was incredible..'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  In BTM Stage 1 , was wandering when we found a new outlet serving Waffles. Tried their waffle which was really nice and they gave it in 99 rs. Good value for money I guess . The manager was courteous enough to offer us a new item for.feedback as they are planning to introduce in the menu. It's called Panner Masaman Crepe . Well it was delicious as it has multiple taste and was yummy . I am sure it will do well . Thanks ."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  It's a newly opened outlet, serving waffles and Crepes . And also Thickshakes . Tried the Choco Drizzle waffle and Berry Blast Thickshakes. It was awesome. The shake was very tasty and thick consistency was there . The waffle was crispy and chocolaty . And all came in 168.. Great.."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A choco base crepe with fresh banana garnished with strawberry spread and a wedge of lime... This is what I ordered at Choc-o-Cheese today. I went to this place after hearing some great things about this place from a friend. I had to try it out once and man was I delighted by their innovation. Arguably the best place in Bangalore to have sweet crepes! The team plans to launch more surprises in the coming months. All the best guys and keep up the great work.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Tried the Fiery Paneer Crepe .Must say it is a different type food. The crepe was sweet and the stuffings were spicy but overall the taste combination was great . You get a mouthful of vivid taste ..And they also a varieties of sauces.. Great place.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A worth visit . Very recently had the Nutella Banana crepe from choc-o-cheese. As a reviewer I would focus on three things- novelty, taste, and affordability. On all three factors, the owner has nailed it. Crepes are a novelty product in Bangalore, very few places serve them. So to have crepes as a product line surely makes this outlet a true innovator. The taste was delicious- very subtle texture rich in flavors. The Nutella banana combination together with light vanilla fragrance would make me go back to them everyday. Third, affordability... To price such an item for just 99 is simply irresistible. You cannot ask for more. Terrific job Team Choc-o-Cheese. Kudos to you..'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Tried savory waffle for the first time. Never knew it could be so great. Waffle was always a sweet delight for me but this was a crunchy delight with mayonnaise Chipotle and lots of veggies making a perfect snacks .
This shops seems to have a huge potential as the items are of international standards support the desi taste buds.. A lot of things to try out. Tried 2 Chipotle Veggies which was sufficient for 2 and it cost us 158 only, also the owner gave us extra toppings and a complimentary strawberry milkshake.. We found them prepare the milkshake using rich cream milk and understood they do not compromise on the quality.
It's a steal in BTM ..
Grab it guys ..."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Really love their Choco Drizzle Waffle . Filled with chocolate sauce and yes it's like yummy , with chocolate coming out of the waffle and has stuffings like choco chips , gems , and some nuts and other things which was very good . They said the waffle is home-made and they have their own secret recipes . Its a good affair ."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Will give a super thumps up to the team for their great work. A young team , innovated waffles in such a manner.. a must try..
Surprised by their menu ordered Paneer Waffle in Tandoori sauce. An absolute astonishing think and eventually a great indeed . Prices is competitive too. Kudos to the team..'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Well a great discovery called Choco cheese in BTM . Well it's not a waffle shop as it dominantly sell Crepes , however we tried waffles and they make it perfect .
We ordered Choco Drizzle with Ice cream. Filled with Nutella chocolate sauce , chocolate ice cream , Chocolate dressings , chocolate chips and Cadbury gems .. It was a blessing for a chocolate lover and it's simply wwow..
We will surely come back"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A young place at heart of the BTM.
Tried Crepes for the first time and it supposed to be a new addition in your bucket list if you have not yet tasted .
A simple Nutella Banana Crepe tasted Very subtle and delicious. Hot crepes and melted chocolate in your mouth is something very interesting.
The owner and the staff are very humble and they have put their heart and soul in their place .

  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it!   We recently visited the Koramangala outlet of BobÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x92s Bar and frankly speaking we were quite impressed. Both food and drinks are very reasonably priced. We had yummy military style Liver masala

  Not every often I give out 5 stars to a place but this place deserves every bit of it!
Located in Koramangala 7th main, diagonally opposite to Fenny's, this is a place for one and all.

Ambience: 4/5
It has sort of an indoor and outdoor seating arrangements. Gives the look of a cafe, comfortable and cozy.

Staff: 5/5
Extremely courteous. Prompt service. You'd happily pay the extra service charge added in the bill.

They serve Jack Daniels Fire at 195!
Glenfiddich at 200ish!
Same is the case with food.

Food: 4/5

If you're looking for a place which serves nachos and fries, this isn't the place for you!

Things we tried: 6-8 Beer, Pork chilly, beef chilly, Peanut masala, Naked Anjal fish fry, Grilled prawns!

And guess our bill?
2000 bucks!

Try out this place to believe it!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

  I was just travelling to Koramangala for the business meeting and looking for a north Indian food and bump into the house of chaaps.   Saw a Facebook post about the place, dropped by this Sunday got a take away, I ordered an Afghani tikka, a hariyali tikka and a gravy. The owner added a few roomali rotis. The food was really good and authentic I'd be definitely going back for more."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  What a great experience this turned out to be. Khichiya is a delectable, yummilicious snack food- a twist on tradition that's both healthy and tasty, without being weird.

The owner was very sweet and explained me all the variants available and how they put it together. Khichiyas are basically a healthy papad with sumptuous toppings from Gujarati/Jain/Rajasthani and other cuisines. There's also a Mexican Khichiya, which looks like a pizza on papad (!), cheese et all.

I'll be coming back for more !"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.
Greek salad - Lettuce, Olives and Feta Cheese in the perfect mix.
Vergin Fried chicken - Chicken Fried with a coated batter. Tasted good.
Mix sause pasta - Penne Rigate Pasta with chicken cubes in a mixed sauce.
3 cheese pesto pizza - Generous servings of Cheddar, Parmesan and Mozarella Cheese layered on the Thin crust Pizza base tasted really well. You could feel the Cheese in every bite.
Chicken wrap - Chicken Cubes with veggies wrapped in Arabian Bread.
Chicken Nachos - Julienned chicken pieces and cheesw spread on Crisp Nachos.
Chicken pot rice - Jasmine rice with a mild Green Curry Gravy with veggies. Very flavourful and tasty.
Prawns kudla de Fogg - A preparation similar to the Prawns Ghee Roast with a similar texture and taste.
Excellent service and good food. Had a pleasant experience.

foodnwine.in'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  I have never had so many different kinds of chicken and all so tasty in one night ever before! You must try their sesame chicken, Chicken Tikka, Afghani Chicken and thin crust Pizzas!

Eye catching location, Amazing food, nice ambience and good music, they have it all!Their drinks are mind blowingly smooth and very well decorated!

  Well say hello to this new kid in the block when you wanna have a drinks night or hang out with your friends for sheesha..

The signature cocktails are amazing and u recommend the white rum and jaggery cocktail, best out of the lot.

For the food options, the place serves everything from finger food to pizza to Indian mains.

To finger point i had the most amazing Aglio Olio here when I have never liked it anywhere in the past.

The pizzas are thin crust and straight out of the woodfired oven. Also they serve the double layer pizzas which doubles your happu. Must try...

Starters are really nice and has extensive spread to go with the drinks.

In mains i liked hakka noodles, paneer makhani served with saffron rice which is prepared on point.

  You just can't take your eyes away from this place which serves yummy Chinese food .Mind-blowing setup with amazing lightings.i love the colours used in the place.

  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

  What a great experience this turned out to be. Khichiya is a delectable, yummilicious snack food- a twist on tradition that's both healthy and tasty, without being weird.

The owner was very sweet and explained me all the variants available and how they put it together. Khichiyas are basically a healthy papad with sumptuous toppings from Gujarati/Jain/Rajasthani and other cuisines. There's also a Mexican Khichiya, which looks like a pizza on papad (!), cheese et all.

  Seafood soup - A Thai Soup with Shrimps and Squids and had a good taste.

  I rarely give out 5/5s on zomato but Bob's bar in Koramangala completely deserves it! A new outlet of Byg Brewski's taproom venture at Indiranagar, Bob's bar offers you exquisite south Indian food with a wide range of options you can pick from. The best part is that you can grab your meals in half plates and full plates - that way you can try out as many possible dishes! My absolute favorite here was the Chilli Pork Baffat which was extremely rich in flavour and went perfectly well with the drinks. Next top pick would be the Mysusru Highway Kheema dosa served with podi amd chutney. We also tried their Malanad Pork and Chicken wings, but weren't very satisfied with them. They have some lovely options for soup as well, and their rasam was simply the perfect blend of spices. The service is quick, the portions are filling and the ambience is calm - all for a cost of two at Rs. 1000/-! Bob's bar is a must visit for all!

address: The Bohemian House, 5, Raja Ram Mohan Roy Road, Richmond Road, Bangalore
name: Third Wave Coffee Roasters @ The Bohemian House
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I love third wave ever since they opened their first branch. There was an event going on so I won't ding them this time on slower service and some chaos. The Vietnamese coffee is the best I've had in town and the coffee with peanut butter drink absolutely delicious. Their fries were crispy and well seasoned and the cheese garlic toast really good specifically the crusty aromatic bread with generous melty cheese. The apple pie was out of Thai world though I would encourage the establishment to get nicer ice cream to go with it. The quiche while too salty had a great crust and filling so may trie it again. The bagel is among the best availible though quite pricy for a bread.
Ambiance my only complaint was no netting so seeds and even bird poop at one point fell onto our table and plate. Should have option of umprella or something.

Food 4.5/5
Service 3/5
Ambiance 4/5
Price 3.5/5")]
