dish_liked: Biryani
cuisines: Biryani, Chinese, North Indian, South Indian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Done and dusted. Never going back here the food is just horrible. Buttermilk and kheema balls are such a disaster. I'm not sure how they have lasted this long in the market. DO NOT RECOMMEND. OVERALL HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable. Although its a busy place but no one will bother you. Kudos to the staff for getting everything on time, you just need to ask them once. I ordered 2 chicken boneless biryani and it was good. It would be great to come here during the day and try out their thali once.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Went for a weekday lunch. Ordered Mutton Biryani and Pomfret. Biryani was okay, but the Fish smelled and was dry. Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is a newly opened outlet of thalappakatti in Trinity circle.. The place is quite small. But gets pretty crowded during lunch. The waiting time is a good half hour if you reach there after 1.30pm.
The service is quite fast and prompt.
We ordered lamb chops, where the mutton was well seasoned and tender, the kottu porotta was mushy and and tasted blank, we then ordered mutton and chicken boneless biriyani both tasted decently good but way too oily. There was always something missing taste wise,in all the dishes I had. The biriyani quantity is good enough to share with another person but not the starters.
I felt that the food was overly priced.')]

name: By Chance
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Stumbled on to this new place "By Chance" pun intended Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82ÃÂ°Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x9fÃ\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x98Ã\x83Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x83Ã\x82Ã\x82Ã\x8e. To sum it up - BEST DECISION EVER.

The experience on the whole was absolutely blissful. Our server Emmanuel, took care of us so well, super polite and efficient service. Mr. Raj was even nice enough to come check on our meal to see if all was well. The pizzeria staff ensure that the chicken tikka pizza we ordered was cooked to perfection. We also ordered Lemon Chicken and Chicken Fried Rice, which was portioned adequately for 2 people, seasoned perfectly and definitely worth the money.

In a nutshell:

Service: 5/5
Taste: 5/5
Value for Money: 5/5 without happy hours
Ambience: 4/5 the place is gorgeous, but the music can be better.

MUST VISIT if you are ever on brigade road.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Aptly named considering we actually found this place by chance. Brigade road was in need of a good gastropub and it looks like it finally has one

The staff are extremely helpful and the prices were surprisingly very pocket friendly for such prime location

I was very impressed with the pizza we ordered. It tasted like woodfire baked pizza and indeed they have a brick oven in their kitchen I noticed later.

I can only see good things for this place if it continues at this level of service and Taste')]

address: 14, Commercial Street, Bangalore
name: Bhartiya Jalpan
reviews_list: [('Rated 5.0', 'RATED\n  I have been to BJP Indiranagar numerous times and the taste and quality of their food never fails to amaze me...I had been waiting to visit their new outlet and God is it good! Finger looking good...i tried their kulcha meal which comes with paneer and dal...this plate can compete with any of the top fine dining places in terms of taste! I am a tea person and not a milk person but on a friends recommendation tried their badam milk and am now wondering how I am not a milk person! If you have been to the other outlet you already know their pav bhaji, tikki chola are all time favourites. All in all you wont regret trying this place and once you do you will come back for more :)'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED\n  A no frills, self service place in the heart of commercial street, ideal for shoppers preferring light eats, chaats or even thalis. We liked the masala Pepsi but the quantity was less. We ordered samosa & dhokla which were good with the chutneys on offer. Overall good & light on pocket.')]

reviews_list:

  The quantity of food which I got today will not even fill a 5 years old child stomach, and the raita which you charged extra 10 rs was water not raita so please don't fool people"), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Its Not that much Tasty, no salt at all ordered 3 varieties biryanis all three dont has salt at all and too much oil in boneless biryani and prawn biryani'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Had ordered full biryani, what I got was a quarter plate biryani which was not even sufficient for 6 year old kid . You can say rice was not more than 7 spoons and chicken piece was one 20-25g small piece.

When checked with restaurant through zomato, I was being told this is the standard quantity. If you don't understand what I am stating here then you can suppose if you have order paneer curry then you will get 2 small pieces of paneer on the order and restaurant would justify this is their standard quantity.

THIS IS BEST RESTAURANT TO TASTE THE FOOD AS THEY PROVIDE ONLY THIS MUCH QUANTITY"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Quantity very less as compared to the price. I placed an mutton biryani order online and received just biryani without raita.
Taste was okay not that great. Will not recommend it.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Was searching for nice Hyderabadi biryani. visited Kitchens@Whitefield and checked multiple options before this place
1st - I was very much impressed with the hospitality of Mr. Noor at Biryani Nation. 
2nd - He allowed me to check small portion before ordering - Tasted authentic, properly cooked 
3rd - Showed me the packing material (250ml, 500ml, 1000ml) -  was nice and Hygienic 
With no further thoughts ordered Boneless Chicken Biryani , Leg Piece Biryani and Veg Dum Biryani for my Team. all 1000ml packs for 25 people all together. The food was ready on time for pickup.

name: Third Wave Coffee Roasters @ The Bohemian House
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I love third wave ever since they opened their first branch. There was an event going on so I won't ding them this time on slower service and some chaos. The Vietnamese coffee is the best I've had in town and the coffee with peanut butter drink absolutely delicious. Their fries were crispy and well seasoned and the cheese garlic toast really good specifically the crusty aromatic bread with generous melty cheese. The apple pie was out of Thai world though I would encourage the establishment to get nicer ice cream to go with it. The quiche while too salty had a great crust and filling so may trie it again. The bagel is among the best availible though quite pricy for a bread.
Ambiance my only complaint was no netting so seeds and even bird poop at one point fell onto our table and plate. Should have option of umprella or something.

Food 4.5/5
Service 3/5
Ambiance 4/5
Price 3.5/5")]

address: 295/296, Ground Floor, 100 Feet Road, Indiranagar, Bengaluru
name: The Twisted Desi
dish_liked: Vegetable Biryani, Dal Makhani, Matar Methi Malai, Pasta, Rasmalai, Gulab Jamun, Dal Tadka
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The Twisted Desi is a newly opened pure veg restaurant adjacent to TOIT in the same building as of Bathinda Dine on the ground floor. They can accommodate around 35 people at a time. The ambiance is pretty bright which gives soothing and relaxing vibes.

I visited this place last week with a bunch of friends. Basically, they have tried to twist the conventional Continental, Italian, North Indian, Chinese Cuisines in a unique way that is interesting.

For the first time in Bangalore, I could get an authentic North Indian (Punjabi) Main Course food which had real flavors.

The juice beverages are very original and have real fruits or other components. The food items I would recommend you to try: Cream of Broccoli Soup (served with special kind of butter bread crumbs), Aloo Chaat, Mix Veg Cutlet, Italian Pulao, Dal Makhani, Dal Tadka, Rasmali Neptune and Twisted Gulab Jamun.

The staff was courteous and served well.

Prices are nominal and they have Zomato Gold on Food.

thedelighttable.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Twisted desi is a heaven for Veggies and as the name suggests there is twisted desi foods.Interiors are very attractive and can accomodate around 30_35 pax .Recently tried here for a dinner and that was a perfect one.

We tried few and they are,

1) Cream of Brocolli : Creamy and refresh the taste buds .Must try*

2) Avo California: Best presentation and it is made up of  diced avocado and apple tossed with lemon juice.

3)Paneer Tikka: Must try,one of my fav here.

4)Lacha Paratha & Dal Makhani : Best combination and well prepared.

5)Italian Pulao: Twisted pulao (something different & unique)

6) Rasmali : Siganture dessert with  catchy presentation.Perfect one.

7)Veg Cutlet: Heart shaped crispy cutlet

8) Dry Fruit Milkshake: Best !

9) Gulab Jamun : Yummy

NB : Veggies don't miss out to try here.

Ambience :5/5
Food:5/5

address: 18, Ramashree Arcade, MG Road, Bangalore
name: Dindigul Thalappakatti
dish_liked: Biryani, Fish, Pepper Chicken
cuisines: Biryani, Chinese, North Indian, South Indian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Part of a 60-year chain that has opened a couple of places in Bangalore and serves good biriyani. Right spice levels + good quality boneless meat + flavourful rice make it quite a good choice, a lot different from the ubiquitous Andhra biriyani.
They have some good side dishes as well, though most of them seem to be available only in the evenings. We tried the Liver Roast and it was very good.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Was waiting to try this after hearing a lot from tamil nadu about it . But the taste is average . The chicken biryani dint have much flavours n no spice at all . The pomfret steamed fish was good n spicy n lot of quantity .'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Done and dusted. Never going back here the food is just horrible. Buttermilk and kheema balls are such a disaster. I'm not sure how they have lasted this long in the market. DO NOT RECOMMEND. OVERALL HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable. Although its a busy place but no one will bother you. Kudos to the staff for getting everything on time, you just need to ask them once. I ordered 2 chicken boneless biryani and it was good. It would be great to come here during the day and try out their thali once.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Went for a weekday lunch. Ordered Mutton Biryani and Pomfret. Biryani was okay, but the Fish smelled and was dry. Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is a newly opened outlet of thalappakatti in Trinity circle.. The place is quite small. But gets pretty crowded during lunch. The waiting time is a good half hour if you reach there after 1.30pm.
The service is quite fast and prompt.
We ordered lamb chops, where the mutton was well seasoned and tender, the kottu porotta was mushy and and tasted blank, we then ordered mutton and chicken boneless biriyani both tasted decently good but way too oily. There was always something missing taste wise,in all the dishes I had. The biriyani quantity is good enough to share with another person but not the starters.
I felt that the food was overly priced.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A small food joint located on the beautiful church street, we just accidentally stumbled upon this place and thought of giving it a try.

We ordered a veg haka noodles, gobhi manchurian and chilli chicken. Although the food was served after 15 minutes or so, the taste made it up for the wait. The noodles were delicious, the gobhi manchurian was super yummy, and the owner of the place offered to charge only 50% the value of gobhi manchurian ciz according to him the quantity was a bit less in that, the chilli chicken was finger licking good.

The pricing is amazing, the feel of the church street with this delicious food makes it a super hit formula.

A must try place.')]

address: The Bohemian House, 5, Raja Ram Mohan Roy Road, Richmond Road, Bangalore
name: Third Wave Coffee Roasters @ The Bohemian House
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I love third wave ever since they opened their first branch. There was an event going on so I won't ding them this time on slower service and some chaos. The Vietnamese coffee is the best I've had in town and the coffee with peanut butter drink absolutely delicious. Their fries were crispy and well seasoned and the cheese garlic toast really good specifically the crusty aromatic bread with generous melty cheese. The apple pie was out of Thai world though I would encourage the establishment to get nicer ice cream to go with it. The quiche while too salty had a great crust and filling so may trie it again. The bagel is among the best availible though quite pricy for a bread.
Ambiance my only complaint was no netting so seeds and even bird poop at one point fell onto our table and plate. Should have option of umprella or something.

Food 4.5/5
Service 3/5
Ambiance 4/5
Price 3.5/5")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Part of a 60-year chain that has opened a couple of places in Bangalore and serves good biriyani. Right spice levels + good quality boneless meat + flavourful rice make it quite a good choice, a lot different from the ubiquitous Andhra biriyani.
They have some good side dishes as well, though most of them seem to be available only in the evenings. We tried the Liver Roast and it was very good.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable.   This is a newly opened outlet of thalappakatti in Trinity circle.. The place is quite small. But gets pretty crowded during lunch. The waiting time is a good half hour if you reach there after 1.30pm.

We ordered lamb chops, where the mutton was well seasoned and tender, the kottu porotta was mushy and and tasted blank, we then ordered mutton and chicken boneless biriyani both tasted decently good but way too oily. There was always something missing taste wise,in all the dishes I had. The biriyani quantity is good enough to share with another person but not the starters.

address: 956, 12th Main Road, Off 100 Feet Road, Indiranagar, Bangalore
name: Sunny's
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is round 2, attempt 2 for Sunny's in Indiranagar.
The first time they abruptly shut down.
Here is to a better round two.
They've opened in a new location right next to Plan B on 12th Main.
The Google maps location might say otherwise.
They do not have an alcohol license yet but that's understandable , I'm guessing it takes time.
However it does take away from the quintessential Sunny's experience.
Kinda makes me feel that this might be the reason why the place was almost 70% empty as well on a Saturday night.
The food was amazing and right up there with the Sunny's that we all like and go too.
I had the Chicken Saltimbocca - was amazing
Friend had the Chicken Diane - was good.
And the Gluten Free 4 cheese Pizza - the fact that it was gluten free made it a little chewy , but good all the same.
For desert we had the Paris Brest ( Strawberry )
Over all good experience and amazing service!
Keep it up guys !")]

  The Twisted Desi is a newly opened pure veg restaurant adjacent to TOIT in the same building as of Bathinda Dine on the ground floor. They can accommodate around 35 people at a time. The ambiance is pretty bright which gives soothing and relaxing vibes.

I visited this place last week with a bunch of friends. Basically, they have tried to twist the conventional Continental, Italian, North Indian, Chinese Cuisines in a unique way that is interesting.

For the first time in Bangalore, I could get an authentic North Indian (Punjabi) Main Course food which had real flavors.

The juice beverages are very original and have real fruits or other components. The food items I would recommend you to try: Cream of Broccoli Soup (served with special kind of butter bread crumbs), Aloo Chaat, Mix Veg Cutlet, Italian Pulao, Dal Makhani, Dal Tadka, Rasmali Neptune and Twisted Gulab Jamun.

The staff was courteous and served well.

Prices are nominal and they have Zomato Gold on Food.

address: 956, 12th Main Road, Off 100 Feet Road, Indiranagar, Bangalore
name: Sunny's
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is round 2, attempt 2 for Sunny's in Indiranagar.
The first time they abruptly shut down.
Here is to a better round two.
They've opened in a new location right next to Plan B on 12th Main.
The Google maps location might say otherwise.
They do not have an alcohol license yet but that's understandable , I'm guessing it takes time.
However it does take away from the quintessential Sunny's experience.
Kinda makes me feel that this might be the reason why the place was almost 70% empty as well on a Saturday night.
The food was amazing and right up there with the Sunny's that we all like and go too.
I had the Chicken Saltimbocca - was amazing
Friend had the Chicken Diane - was good.
And the Gluten Free 4 cheese Pizza - the fact that it was gluten free made it a little chewy , but good all the same.
For desert we had the Paris Brest ( Strawberry )
Over all good experience and amazing service!
Keep it up guys !")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is round 2, attempt 2 for Sunny's in Indiranagar.
The first time they abruptly shut down.
Here is to a better round two.
They've opened in a new location right next to Plan B on 12th Main.
The Google maps location might say otherwise.
They do not have an alcohol license yet but that's understandable , I'm guessing it takes time.
However it does take away from the quintessential Sunny's experience.
Kinda makes me feel that this might be the reason why the place was almost 70% empty as well on a Saturday night.
The food was amazing and right up there with the Sunny's that we all like and go too.
I had the Chicken Saltimbocca - was amazing
Friend had the Chicken Diane - was good.
And the Gluten Free 4 cheese Pizza - the fact that it was gluten free made it a little chewy , but good all the same.
For desert we had the Paris Brest ( Strawberry )
Over all good experience and amazing service!
Keep it up guys !")]

address: 956, 12th Main Road, Off 100 Feet Road, Indiranagar, Bangalore
name: Sunny's
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is round 2, attempt 2 for Sunny's in Indiranagar.
The first time they abruptly shut down.
Here is to a better round two.
They've opened in a new location right next to Plan B on 12th Main.
The Google maps location might say otherwise.
They do not have an alcohol license yet but that's understandable , I'm guessing it takes time.
However it does take away from the quintessential Sunny's experience.
Kinda makes me feel that this might be the reason why the place was almost 70% empty as well on a Saturday night.
The food was amazing and right up there with the Sunny's that we all like and go too.
I had the Chicken Saltimbocca - was amazing
Friend had the Chicken Diane - was good.
And the Gluten Free 4 cheese Pizza - the fact that it was gluten free made it a little chewy , but good all the same.
For desert we had the Paris Brest ( Strawberry )
Over all good experience and amazing service!
Keep it up guys !")]

  Firstly, the place is fairly new and they are trying to build the place up and make it consistent in their service. As of now, the place gave me good vibes and looked like it could grow out to be a nice place to eat dinner or lunch at. The atmosphere is nothing different than any other restaurant that you would see and the service was on point. Coming to the food, the starters that we ordered was just great and even the fresh lime soda too. Talking about the main course, the generic Indian breads were tasty and I would suggest you to buy the garlic naan and masala kulcha, but the chicken in the curry was not at all fresh and it had a very peculiar taste to it which was not very pleasant to eat at all. I thought this problem was only with the two curries I ordered because the starters tasted great. There are no desserts here, like ice creams or anything which was a big downside. I feel that this place has good potential for growth and would recommend people to go here.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I tried Shawarma roll here, it was okay. Nothing to rave about.

address: 25-27, Margosa Road, Malleshwaram Bengalore
name: Vijayalakshmi Veg
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A place where it's tough to find place during peak hours, always crowded because of many commercial establishments near by. Khali dosa, rava dosa, masala dosa, rava idli, roti curry and madhur vada are according to me must try."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place for a small bites and food. Overall well managed. I liked the place for the coffee

There are areas of improvement which can be worked on.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  My search for Vazhakkai Bajji in Bangalore finally ends at Vijay Lakshmi restaurant. Fairly a new place but seems to already attract crowd for food, tiffin and coffee. Visited the place around 1:30pm and the restaurant was serving lunch as well as tiffin / snacks. The snacks are neatly displayed at the glass counter and there I found my favourite Vazhakkai bajji that I have been fanatically searching for quite sometime and trust me, I am not disappointed at all, its one of the best bajji's I have ever had. The restaurant is neat and tidy. No seating place available however table counters are there where one can stand and eat. Other than bajji , we had dosa, Kara baath and filter coffee which were good too. I am definitely visiting the place again for some appetizing food.")]

address: The Bohemian House, 5, Raja Ram Mohan Roy Road, Richmond Road, Bangalore
name: Third Wave Coffee Roasters @ The Bohemian House
reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I love third wave ever since they opened their first branch. There was an event going on so I won't ding them this time on slower service and some chaos. The Vietnamese coffee is the best I've had in town and the coffee with peanut butter drink absolutely delicious. Their fries were crispy and well seasoned and the cheese garlic toast really good specifically the crusty aromatic bread with generous melty cheese. The apple pie was out of Thai world though I would encourage the establishment to get nicer ice cream to go with it. The quiche while too salty had a great crust and filling so may trie it again. The bagel is among the best availible though quite pricy for a bread.
Ambiance my only complaint was no netting so seeds and even bird poop at one point fell onto our table and plate. Should have option of umprella or something.

Food 4.5/5
Service 3/5
Ambiance 4/5
Price 3.5/5")]

address: 18, Ramashree Arcade, MG Road, Bangalore
name: Dindigul Thalappakatti
dish_liked: Biryani, Fish, Pepper Chicken
cuisines: Biryani, Chinese, North Indian, South Indian
reviews_list:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It was meeting a friend after a long time, Have heard about it's non veg delicacy but thought of trying veg today. The Ambiance was good, during lunch u need to wait for ur turn. I got a place to sit after a 10mins wait which was OK with me.

We ordered Mushroom Pepper, Paneer Tikka, Paneer Biriyani and Fresh lime soda.

I must say the Mushroom Pepper was sucluent and spices and peeper kicked in the right way. Paneer Tikka was soft well cooked and went good with the mint chutney and pickeled onion. Paneer Biriyani was a bit spicy but no regrets.

Will definitely come again for putting my hands on for NonVeg too.

Quality and Quantity was perfect."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Part of a 60-year chain that has opened a couple of places in Bangalore and serves good biriyani. Right spice levels + good quality boneless meat + flavourful rice make it quite a good choice, a lot different from the ubiquitous Andhra biriyani.
They have some good side dishes as well, though most of them seem to be available only in the evenings. We tried the Liver Roast and it was very good.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Was waiting to try this after hearing a lot from tamil nadu about it . But the taste is average . The chicken biryani dint have much flavours n no spice at all . The pomfret steamed fish was good n spicy n lot of quantity .'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Done and dusted. Never going back here the food is just horrible. Buttermilk and kheema balls are such a disaster. I'm not sure how they have lasted this long in the market. DO NOT RECOMMEND. OVERALL HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The place was swamped and the staff is great. Everything was handled very well. We were asked to wait for 10 mins and trust me it was worth the wait. We sat down and the seats were comfortable. Although its a busy place but no one will bother you. Kudos to the staff for getting everything on time, you just need to ask them once. I ordered 2 chicken boneless biryani and it was good. It would be great to come here during the day and try out their thali once.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Went for a weekday lunch. Ordered Mutton Biryani and Pomfret. Biryani was okay, but the Fish smelled and was dry. Also, as the crowd increased, the staff got impatient and served us Biryani despite its asking for extra time to finish the Fish. They were keen on getting us out, and getting the next customers in -- which is understandable, but shouldn't be shown like that."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is a newly opened outlet of thalappakatti in Trinity circle.. The place is quite small. But gets pretty crowded during lunch. The waiting time is a good half hour if you reach there after 1.30pm.
The service is quite fast and prompt.
We ordered lamb chops, where the mutton was well seasoned and tender, the kottu porotta was mushy and and tasted blank, we then ordered mutton and chicken boneless biriyani both tasted decently good but way too oily. There was always something missing taste wise,in all the dishes I had. The biriyani quantity is good enough to share with another person but not the starters.
I felt that the food was overly priced.')]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I love third wave ever since they opened their first branch. There was an event going on so I won't ding them this time on slower service and some chaos. The Vietnamese coffee is the best I've had in town and the coffee with peanut butter drink absolutely delicious. Their fries were crispy and well seasoned and the cheese garlic toast really good specifically the crusty aromatic bread with generous melty cheese. The apple pie was out of Thai world though I would encourage the establishment to get nicer ice cream to go with it. The quiche while too salty had a great crust and filling so may trie it again. The bagel is among the best availible though quite pricy for a bread.
Ambiance my only complaint was no netting so seeds and even bird poop at one point fell onto our table and plate. Should have option of umprella or something.

Food 4.5/5
Service 3/5
Ambiance 4/5
Price 3.5/5")]

  It was meeting a friend after a long time, Have heard about it's non veg delicacy but thought of trying veg today. The Ambiance was good, during lunch u need to wait for ur turn. I got a place to sit after a 10mins wait which was OK with me.

I must say the Mushroom Pepper was sucluent and spices and peeper kicked in the right way. Paneer Tikka was soft well cooked and went good with the mint chutney and pickeled onion. Paneer Biriyani was a bit spicy but no regrets.

Will definitely come again for putting my hands on for NonVeg too.

Quality and Quantity was perfect."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Delightfully surprising!! One always felt that there is a serious lack of food options while shopping in Commercial street. Today while on the shopping spree we bumped into this outlet.

reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Only restaurant in Sompura or south of Bangalore which offers English breakfast in the morning.

Chicken Alfam is a must try.

address: Arya Hub Mall, 12/2, 13/1B, ITBP Main Road, Prashanth Extension, Whitefield, Bangalore
name: Potful
dish_liked: Hyderabadi Biryani, Rumali Roti, Raita
reviews_list:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  I had ordered a couple of times from this outlet .Food quality is decent but was surprised to see the change in quantity and pot size for same Hyderabadi chicken Biryani Pics attached.It was sufficient for 2-3 people but now hardly 2 people can have it.Not going to try again'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Craving for a good biryani can lead you to try biryani from umpteen places. On a Friday evening I decided to order biryani from potful.

The concept of the pot made me more excited to give this place a try.

After alot of thinking I decided to order the hyderbadi biryani both veg and non veg.

And myself being half Hyderabadi I had high hopes from it.

And the order was delivered well on time and couldn't wait to dig in.

Beautifully seal packed. The pots arrived. Had to taste the food right away. The first bite and I couldn't stop myself from having the whole pot myself.

Also I tasted the chicken kada masala starter. Oh yum !

I'm going to order very frequently from here."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Potful serves authentic Biryani cooked in a clay pot and directly delivered to your home. They ensure that the Biryani you get is 100% safe and untouched.
I had ordered Lucknowi Chicken Biryani and my experience from unpacking it to taking the first bite was amazing. The range of flavours and the aroma coming from the Biryani were fabulous. Along with the Biryani, I had ordered Murgh Khada Masala. It had a smokey taste and it worked great as a starter.
Potful Biryani was by far one of the best Biryanis that I've eaten in Bangalore.

In a nutshell, Potful doesn't only provide Biryani. They provide a wonderful experience and Biryani is just a beautiful part of it.

A MUST TRY FOR EVERY BIRYANI LOVER!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I'm a big fan of potful claypot biryani's and have tried from their various outlets and glad to share that all of them are keeping up with the quality and quantity standards. The pot is sealed with wheat dough to allow it to cook in its own steam thus keeping the rice and veggies tender and juicy and it is not opened until it is ready to serve, you can get a feel of authentic biryani from the aroma itself. With every bite, you can feel a million flavors reaching your taste buds. Biryani is accompanied with fresh onion and cucumber raita. This time I ordered kali Mirch paneer tikka as well which was well grilled and juicy. Overall, a wonderful experience every single time!! Will always be back for more."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Its been a long time since I have been wanting to try the Lucknowi style biryani as we have had Hyderabadi only most of the time. The clay pot biryani served here attracted me and we decided to go for it.

We ordered -
Kali mirch lasooni paneer tikka - Six pieces of paneer tikka served with a green chutney and marinated onions. Mildly flavoured paneer went quite well with the chutney but the paneer could have been a bit softer.

Lucknowi mix veg biryani - The biryani itself is served in a clay pot with the traditional sealing and all. It took us a while to remove the seal. The biryani was hot and full of the flavour of the clay pot itself. Quite a decent amount of gravy and veggies and the rice was long grained and fluffy. Served with raita, the amount of biryani served was more than enough for two people with moderate appetites. Quite an enjoyable meal.

parkstreet19.wordpress.com'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I ordered lucknowi mix veg Biryani, lasooni paneer tikka and raita recently from this place. I wanted to try claypot biryani from a long time. I loved the biryani. It was rich in flavours, the masalas were really good. It was really tasty and delivered hot. The paneer tikka was average and lacked flavours or marination. Could have been better.
Overall it was really good, delivered on time and food was hot and fresh!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I ordered Lukhnawi Chicken Biryani from this place and it was my first time to try Claypot biryani. I really liked the packaging, and it was quite hot when it was delivered to me. It came with a small portion of raitha. Raitha was good, but the quantity was very less for the portion of biryani.

The quantity of biryani is way sufficient for two people and it had around 5 good pieces of chicken, so it's price is totally justifiable. Chicken was cooked properly but it was little dry for me, but overall taste of biryani is good. I also ordered Murg Khada Masala from the starters, it had six small boneless pieces and according to the price, it is slightly on the higher side.

I really liked the packaging and delivery was dot on time and taste was good too. They have few more options available in biryani, will surely try sometime."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the best biryani in bangalore which provides delivery. [('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  I ordered aloo paratha combo through zomato and it was described as aloo paratha, dal makhani, curd, butter.
But what I got was
Aloo paratha which had more of onion and coriander than aloo, oiled when paratha was raw. So I would rather call it onion paratha. Stuffing had no taste.
Masoor dal in the name of dal makhni, and the dal gravy tasted sour and dal was uncooked.
Curd was thinner than the lasii served normally around with bits and morsels of onion and tomato.
No butter in the packet

Overall highly disappointed with the food I got.
But the packaging was really good and super fast delivery.

Overall
Taste: 1.5/5
Packaging: 5/5
Value for money: 1.5/5 (for the food I was served, quantity was but fine)
Delivery: 5/5

Will I order it again: NOT for the time being at least.')]

  Super tasty food. Value for money. Keep it up. We ordered chicken tried rice, paneer fried rice n gobhi Manchurian. It was yummmm. Will surely look forward to order from here next time'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is a new outlet opened inside Prasanthi complex at Channasandra. So we decided to taste the food for a dinner.
It's a small outlet like others inside the complex with 10 people seating arrangement and all outside seating.

The menu was having lot of dishes specially in non veg dishes and also parathas.
As we packed the food for us the food preparation time was quick.
The staff were humble and were ready to manage slight modifications.

We ordered 4 tandoori rotis ,one chicken gravy and one chilli chicken dry.
The chicken gravy was good in taste with finely sliced onion and garlic with 4 good pieces of chicken.
The chill chicken was also nice with nicely coated chicken pieces and onion & peppers. It was having a good sweet and sour taste.
Some of the tandoori rotis were not cooked properly , I think it was removed from the tandoor too early.

With a very good price tag and tasty food it is recommended...")]

reviews_list:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  I ordered aloo paratha combo through zomato and it was described as aloo paratha, dal makhani, curd, butter.
But what I got was
Aloo paratha which had more of onion and coriander than aloo, oiled when paratha was raw. So I would rather call it onion paratha. Stuffing had no taste.
Masoor dal in the name of dal makhni, and the dal gravy tasted sour and dal was uncooked.
Curd was thinner than the lasii served normally around with bits and morsels of onion and tomato.
No butter in the packet

Overall highly disappointed with the food I got.
But the packaging was really good and super fast delivery.

Overall
Taste: 1.5/5
Packaging: 5/5
Value for money: 1.5/5 (for the food I was served, quantity was but fine)
Delivery: 5/5

Will I order it again: NOT for the time being at least.')]

address: Prashanti Complex, Chanasandra Main Road Whitefield, Bangalore
name: On The Go
reviews_list:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Super tasty food. Value for money. Keep it up. We ordered chicken tried rice, paneer fried rice n gobhi Manchurian. It was yummmm. Will surely look forward to order from here next time'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is a new outlet opened inside Prasanthi complex at Channasandra. So we decided to taste the food for a dinner.
It's a small outlet like others inside the complex with 10 people seating arrangement and all outside seating.

The menu was having lot of dishes specially in non veg dishes and also parathas.
As we packed the food for us the food preparation time was quick.
The staff were humble and were ready to manage slight modifications.

We ordered 4 tandoori rotis ,one chicken gravy and one chilli chicken dry.
The chicken gravy was good in taste with finely sliced onion and garlic with 4 good pieces of chicken.
The chill chicken was also nice with nicely coated chicken pieces and onion & peppers. It was having a good sweet and sour taste.
Some of the tandoori rotis were not cooked properly , I think it was removed from the tandoor too early.

With a very good price tag and tasty food it is recommended...")]
